Name: kAnimatedImageResume
Documentation:
Uses the Resume method instead of the Catch-up method for animated images.
- Catch-up behavior tries to keep animated images in pace with wall-clock
  time. This might require decoding several animation frames if the
  animation has fallen behind.
- Resume behavior presents what would have been the next presented frame.
  This means it might only decode one frame, resuming where it left off.
  However, if the animation updates faster than the display's refresh rate,
  it is possible to decode more than a single frame.

Name: kAvoidUnnecessaryBeforeUnloadCheckPostTask
Documentation:
The following two features, when enabled, result in the browser process only
asking the renderer process to run beforeunload handlers if it knows such
handlers are registered. The two slightly differ in what they do and how
they behave:
. `kAvoidUnnecessaryBeforeUnloadCheckPostTask` in this case content continues
  to report a beforeunload handler is present (even though it isn't). When
  asked to dispatch the beforeunload handler, a post task is used (rather
  than going to the renderer).
. `kAvoidUnnecessaryBeforeUnloadCheckSync` in this case content does not
  report a beforeunload handler is present. A ramification of this is
  navigations that would normally check beforeunload handlers before
  continuing will not, and navigation will synchronously continue.
Only one should be used (if both are set, the second takes precedence). The
second is unsafe for Android WebView (and thus entirely disabled via
ContentBrowserClient::SupportsAvoidUnnecessaryBeforeUnloadCheckSync()),
because the embedder may trigger reentrancy, which cannot be avoided.

Name: kDarkenWebsitesCheckboxInThemesSetting
Documentation: Enables auto dark feature in theme settings.

Name: kDawn2dCanvas
Documentation: Enables Dawn-accelerated 2D canvas.

Name: kDebounceDocumentProvider
Documentation: Feature to debounce drive requests from the document provider.

Name: kDebugHistoryInterventionNoUserActivation
Documentation: Enable debugging the issue crbug.com/1201355

Name: kDecodeJpeg420ImagesToYUV
Documentation:
Decodes jpeg 4:2:0 formatted images to YUV instead of RGBX and stores in this
format in the image decode cache. See crbug.com/919627 for details on the
feature.

Name: kDecodeLossyWebPImagesToYUV
Documentation:
Decodes lossy WebP images to YUV instead of RGBX and stores in this format
in the image decode cache. See crbug.com/900264 for details on the feature.

Name: kDecodeScriptSourceOffThread
Documentation:
If enabled, script source text will be decoded and hashed off the main
thread.

Name: kDecoupleSendTabToSelfAndSyncSettings
Documentation:
Causes the device to be a valid send-tab-to-self target and sender,
regardless of UserSelectableType::kTabs and SyncRequested.

Name: kDefaultANGLEMetal
Documentation: Default to using ANGLE's Metal backend.

Name: kDefaultANGLEOpenGL
Documentation: Default to using ANGLE's OpenGL backend

Name: kDefaultANGLEVulkan
Documentation: Default to using ANGLE's Vulkan backend.

Name: kDefaultChromeAppsMigration
Documentation: Enable force installed Chrome apps policy migration.

Name: kDefaultEnableANGLEValidation
Documentation: Enables the use of ANGLE validation for non-WebGL contexts.

Name: kDefaultEnableGpuRasterization
Documentation:
Enable GPU Rasterization by default. This can still be overridden by
--enable-gpu-rasterization or --disable-gpu-rasterization.
DefaultEnableGpuRasterization has launched on Mac, Windows, ChromeOS,
Android and Linux.

Name: kDefaultPassthroughCommandDecoder
Documentation:
All features in alphabetical order. The features should be documented
alongside the definition of their values in the .cc file.
AboutFlagOs: kOsMac | kOsLinux | kOsLacros | kOsCrOS | kOsAndroid | kOsFuchsia

Name: kDefaultStyleSheetsEarlyInit
Documentation: Initialize CSSDefaultStyleSheets early in renderer startup.

Name: kDefaultTypedNavigationsToHttps
Documentation: Navigation experiments.

Name: kDeferBeginMainFrameDuringLoading
Documentation:
If enabled, the parser may continue parsing if BeginMainFrame was
recently called.

Name: kDelayFirstParkingOfStrings
Documentation:
Enabling this will delay the first aging of strings by 60 seconds instead of
the default. See comment around the use of the feature for the logic behind
the delay.

Name: kDelayLowPriorityRequestsAccordingToNetworkState
Documentation:
If enabled, the ResourceLoadScheculer will take the current network state
into consideration, when it plans to delay a low-priority throttleable
requests in the tight mode. The factors include:
 - The total number of the in-flight multiplexed connections (e.g.,
   H2/SPDY/QUIC).
 - HTTP RTT estimate.

Name: kDelayRequestsOnMultiplexedConnections
Documentation:
When kPriorityRequestsDelayableOnSlowConnections is enabled, HTTP
requests fetched from a SPDY/QUIC/H2 proxies can be delayed by the
ResourceScheduler just as HTTP/1.1 resources are. However, requests from such
servers are not subject to kMaxNumDelayableRequestsPerHostPerClient limit.

Name: kDelayUnsafeAds
Documentation:
Enables the artificial delaying of ads that are considered unsafe (e.g. http
or same-domain to the top-level).

Name: kDelayedWarnings
Documentation: Controls whether the delayed warning experiment is enabled.

Name: kDeleteExpiredDownloads
Documentation: Whether to delete expired download.

Name: kDeleteOverwrittenDownloads
Documentation: Whether to delete downloads that are overwritten by others.

Name: kDeprioritizeDOMTimersDuringPageLoading
Documentation: Deprioritizes JS timer tasks during a particular phase of page loading.

Name: kDesktopCaptureChangeSource
Documentation: Enable changing source dynamically for desktop capture.

Name: kDesktopDetailedLanguageSettings
Documentation: This feature enables setting the application language on Desktop.

Name: kDesktopPWAsAdditionalWindowingControls
Documentation: API that allows PWAs manually minimizing, maximizing and restoring windows.
AboutFlagOs: kOsWin | kOsLinux | kOsLacros | kOsMac | kOsCrOS | kOsFuchsia

Name: kDesktopPWAsCacheDuringDefaultInstall
Documentation:
When installing default installed PWAs, we wait for service workers
to cache resources.

Name: kDesktopPWAsElidedExtensionsMenu
Documentation:
Moves the Extensions "puzzle piece" icon from the title bar into the app menu
for web app windows.

Name: kDesktopPWAsEnforceWebAppSettingsPolicy
Documentation: Whether to parse and enforce the WebAppSettings policy.

Name: kDesktopPWAsRunOnOsLogin
Documentation: Enables or disables Desktop PWAs to be auto-started on OS login.

Name: kDesktopPWAsSubApps
Documentation:
API that allows installed PWAs to add additional shortcuts by means of
installing sub app components.
AboutFlagOs: kOsWin | kOsLinux | kOsLacros | kOsMac | kOsCrOS | kOsFuchsia

Name: kDesktopPWAsTabStrip
Documentation:
Adds a tab strip to PWA windows.
TODO(crbug.com/897314): Enable this feature.

Name: kDesktopPWAsTabStripSettings
Documentation: Adds a user settings that allows PWAs to be opened with a tab strip.

Name: kDesktopPWAsWebBundles
Documentation: Adds support for web bundles, making web apps able to be launched offline.

Name: kDesktopRestructuredLanguageSettings
Documentation:
This feature enables the desktop version's redesigned language settings
layout.

Name: kDesktopScreenshots
Documentation:
Feature flag to enable the screenshots feature, currently accessed only
through the sharing hub.

Name: kDestroyProfileOnBrowserClose
Documentation:
Destroy profiles when their last browser window is closed, instead of when
the browser exits.

Name: kDestroySystemProfiles
Documentation:
DestroyProfileOnBrowserClose only covers deleting regular (non-System)
Profiles. This flags lets us destroy the System Profile, as well.
AboutFlagOs: kOsCrOS | kOsMac | kOsWin | kOsLinux | kOsLacros | kOsFuchsia

Name: kDetailedLanguageSettings
Documentation: This feature enables setting the application language on Android.

Name: kDetectFormSubmissionOnFormClear
Documentation:
Enables submission detection for forms dynamically cleared but not removed
from the page.

Name: kDevicePosture
Documentation:
Enable the device posture API.
Tracking bug for enabling device posture API: https://crbug.com/1066842.

Name: kDialogFocusNewSpecBehavior
Documentation:
When <dialog>s are closed, this focuses the "previously focused" element
which had focus when the <dialog> was first opened.
TODO(crbug.com/649162): Remove DialogFocusNewSpecBehavior after
the feature is in stable with no issues.

Name: kDigitalGoodsApi
Documentation:
Controls whether the Digital Goods API is enabled.
https://github.com/WICG/digital-goods/

Name: kDirectCompositionForceFullDamage
Documentation:
Forces Chrome's main backbuffer to full damage if the actual damage
is large enough and allows DWM to consider the main backbuffer as an
an overlay candidate.

Name: kDirectCompositionLowLatencyPresentation
Documentation: Use presentation feedback event queries (must be enabled) to limit latency.

Name: kDirectCompositionSoftwareOverlays
Documentation:
Allow overlay swapchain to present on all GPUs even if they only support
software overlays. GPU deny lists limit it to NVIDIA only at the moment.

Name: kDirectCompositionVerifyDrawOffset
Documentation:
TODO(crbug.com/1269749): This is used temporarily for verifying
the draw offset bug. The code should be removed once the bug is fixed.

Name: kDisableCGIParamMatching
Documentation: If enabled, suggestions from a cgi param name match are scored to 0.

Name: kDisableDeJelly
Documentation:
Kill-switch to disable de-jelly, even if flags/properties indicate it should
be enabled.

Name: kDisableFairJobScheduling
Documentation:
Under this feature, JobTaskSource doesn't use worker count in its sort key
such that worker threads are not distributed among running jobs equally.

Name: kDisableJobUpdatePriority
Documentation: Under this feature, priority update on Jobs is disabled.

Name: kDisableJobYield
Documentation: Under this feature, ThreadPool::ShouldYield() always returns false

Name: kDisablePrioritizedPostMessageForwarding
Documentation:
Killswitch for prioritizing cross-process postMessage forwarding.

TODO(crbug.com/1212894): Remove after M95.

Name: kDisablePrivacySandboxPrompts
Documentation:
Disables any Privacy Sandbox related prompts. Should only be used for testing
purposes. This feature is used to support external automated testing using
Chrome, where additional prompts break behavior expectations.

Name: kDisableProcessReuse
Documentation:
When enabled, OOPIFs will not try to reuse compatible processes from
unrelated tabs.

Name: kDisableTLSResumption
Documentation: Disables TLS resumption.

Name: kDiscardCodeCacheAfterFirstUse
Documentation:
When enabled, frees up CachedMetadata after consumption by script resources
and modules. Needed for the experiment in http://crbug.com/1045052.

Name: kDiscardableMemoryBackingTrial
Documentation: Feature flag enabling the discardable memory backing trial.

Name: kDiscoFeedEndpoint
Documentation: Use the new DiscoFeed endpoint.

Name: kDiscountConsentV2
Documentation: Feature flag for Discount user consent v2.

Name: kDispatchBeforeUnloadOnFreeze
Documentation:
When enabled, the beforeunload handler is dispatched when a frame is frozen.
This allows the browser to know whether discarding the frame could result in
lost user data, at the cost of extra CPU usage. The feature will be removed
once we have determine whether the CPU cost is acceptable.

Name: kDispatchPopstateSync
Documentation:
Kill switch for firing popstate immediately, instead of deferring it until
after onload.

Name: kDisplayLocking
Documentation: Enable Display Locking JavaScript APIs.

Name: kDisplayTitleForCurrentUrl
Documentation: Feature used to display the title of the current URL match.

Name: kDmTokenDeletion
Documentation:
Causes the DMToken to be deleted (rather than invalidated) when a browser is
deleted from CBCM.

Name: kDnsHttpssvc
Documentation:
Enables DNS query-only experiments for HTTPSSVC or INTEGRITY records,
depending on feature parameters. Received responses never affect Chrome
behavior other than metrics.

Not to be confused with `kUseDnsHttpsSvcb` which is querying HTTPS in order
to affect Chrome connection behavior.

Name: kDnsOverHttps
Documentation: Enable DNS over HTTPS (DoH).

Name: kDnsOverHttpsUpgrade
Documentation: Enable usage of hardcoded DoH upgrade mapping for use in automatic mode.

Name: kDnsTransactionDynamicTimeouts
Documentation:
Support for altering the parameters used for DNS transaction timeout. See
ResolveContext::SecureTransactionTimeout().

Name: kDocumentPolicy
Documentation: Enable document policy for configuring and restricting feature behavior.

Name: kDocumentPolicyNegotiation
Documentation: Enable document policy negotiation mechanism.

Name: kDocumentProvider
Documentation: Document provider

Name: kDocumentProviderAso
Documentation:
Feature to determine a value in the drive request indicating whether the
request should be served by the  ASO backend.

Name: kDocumentTransition
Documentation:
When enabled, permits shared/root element transitions. See
https://github.com/WICG/shared-element-transitions.

Name: kDontSendKeyEventsToJavascript
Documentation:
When enabled, this feature prevent blink sending key event to web unless it
is on installed PWA.

Name: kDownRankJustInTimePaymentApp
Documentation:
If enabled, just-in-time installable payment handlers are ranked lower than
complete autofill instruments in payment sheet's method selection section.

Name: kDownloadAutoResumptionNative
Documentation: Whether download auto-resumptions are enabled in native.

Name: kDownloadBubble
Documentation: Whether to use download bubble instead of download shelf.

Name: kDownloadLater
Documentation: Whether to enable download later feature.

Name: kDownloadRange
Documentation: Arbitrary range request support for download system.

Name: kDownloadServiceFeature
Documentation:
Used to set configuration of download service through Finch. This is not used
to turn on/off the feature.

Name: kDurableClientHintsCache
Documentation: If enabled, the client hints cache will be loaded on browser restarts.

Name: kDurationEstimatesInCompositorTimingHistory
Documentation:
When enabled, CompositorTimingHistory will directly record the timing history
that is used to calculate main thread timing estimates, and use the
percentile of sum of different stages instead of the sum of percentiles.

Name: kDynamicColorGamut
Documentation:
When wide color gamut content from the web is encountered, promote our
display to wide color gamut if supported.

Name: kDynamicMaxAutocomplete
Documentation:
Feature used to cap max suggestions to a dynamic limit based on how many URLs
would be shown. E.g., show up to 10 suggestions if doing so would display no
URLs; else show up to 8 suggestions if doing so would include 1 or more URLs.

Name: kDynamicSchedulerForClients
Documentation: User to parameterize adjustments to clients' deadlines.

Name: kDynamicSchedulerForDraw
Documentation: Used by Viz to parameterize adjustments to scheduler deadlines.

Name: kDynamicSearchUpdateAnimation
Documentation:
Enable shortened search result update animations when in progress animations
are interrupted by search model updates.

Name: kEagerCacheStorageSetupForServiceWorkers
Documentation:
Enable eagerly setting up a CacheStorage interface pointer and
passing it to service workers on startup as an optimization.
TODO(crbug/1077916): Re-enable once the issue with COOP/COEP is fixed.

Name: kEarlyBodyLoad
Documentation: Enables loading the response body earlier in navigation.

Name: kEarlyCodeCache
Documentation: Enables fetching the code cache earlier in navigation.

Name: kEarlyEstablishGpuChannel
Documentation: Enable establishing the GPU channel early in renderer startup.

Name: kEarlyHintsPreloadForNavigation
Documentation: Enable Early Hints subresource preloads for navigation.

Name: kEarlyLibraryLoad
Documentation: Enable loading native libraries earlier in startup on Android.

Name: kEditContext
Documentation:
If enabled, allows web pages to use the experimental EditContext API to
better control text input. See crbug.com/999184.

Name: kElasticOverscroll
Documentation: Cached in Java as well, make sure defaults are updated together.

Name: kElementSuperRareData
Documentation:
This flag makes ElementRareData lazily initialize infrequently used fields as
another class called ElementSuperRareData to improve memory usage.

Name: kElidePrioritizationOfPreNativeBootstrapTasks
Documentation:
Under this flag Java bootstrap (aka startup) tasks that are run before native
initialization will not be specially prioritized by being posted at the front
of the Looper's queue.

Name: kElideTabPreloadAtStartup
Documentation:
Under this flag tab preloading at startup will be elided (i.e., not
performed).

Name: kEmbeddingRequiresOptIn
Documentation:
Requires documents embedded via <iframe>, etc, to explicitly opt-into the
embedding: https://github.com/mikewest/embedding-requires-opt-in.

Name: kEnableAccessibilityAriaVirtualContent
Documentation: Enable recognizing "aria-virtualcontent" as a valid aria property.

Name: kEnableAccessibilityExposeHTMLElement
Documentation:
Enable exposing the <html> element to the browser process AXTree
(as an ignored node).

Name: kEnableAccessibilityExposeIgnoredNodes
Documentation:
Enable exposing ignored nodes from Blink to the browser process AXTree.
This will allow us to simplify logic by eliminating the distiction between
"ignored and included in the tree" from "ignored and not included in the
tree".

Name: kEnableAccessibilityLanguageDetection
Documentation:
Enable language detection to determine language used in page text, exposed
on the browser process AXTree.

Name: kEnableAccessibilityTreeForViews
Documentation:
Serializes accessibility information from the Views tree and deserializes it
into an AXTree in the browser process.

Name: kEnableAggregatedMlSearchRanking
Documentation:
Enables using aggregated model in ranking non-app results for
non empty queries.

Name: kEnableAllSystemWebApps
Documentation:
Enables all registered system web apps, regardless of their respective
feature flags.

Name: kEnableAppListLaunchRecording
Documentation: Enables hashed recording of a app list launches.

Name: kEnableAppRanker
Documentation: Enable app ranking models.

Name: kEnableAppReinstallZeroState
Documentation:
Enables the feature to include a single reinstallation candidate in
zero-state.

Name: kEnableAriaElementReflection
Documentation:
Enable support for ARIA element reflection, for example
element.ariaActiveDescendantElement = child;

Name: kEnableAutomaticSnooze
Documentation:
A feature for enabling automatic snooze mode for In-Product Help (IPH). When
this flag is enabled, we don't show snooze button/UI on the IPH, but on
dismiss we will implicitly snooze it until the snooze limit count is reached.

Name: kEnableBackForwardCacheForScreenReader
Documentation:
Enable back/forward cache for screen reader users. This flag should be
removed once the https://crbug.com/1271450 is resolved.

Name: kEnableBrowsingDataLifetimeManager
Documentation:
Enable BrowsingDataLifetimeManager that periodically delete browsing data as
defined by the BrowsingDataLifetime policy.

Name: kEnableCachedManagementStatus
Documentation: Enable caching the value of the ManagementStatus.

Name: kEnableCanvas2DLayers
Documentation: Enables canvas 2d methods BeginLayer and EndLayer.

Name: kEnableDrDcVulkan
Documentation:
This flag is use additionally with kEnableDrDc to enable the feature for
vulkan enabled android devices.

Name: kEnableExactMatchForNonLatinLocale
Documentation: Enables using exact string search for non latin locales.

Name: kEnableFaviconForPasswords
Documentation: Enables favicons in Password Manager.

Name: kEnableFuzzyAppSearch
Documentation: Enables using the fuzzy search algorithm for app search provider.

Name: kEnableGrShaderCacheForVulkan
Documentation: Enable GrShaderCache to use with Vulkan backend.

Name: kEnableHardwareMirrorMode
Documentation:
A temporary flag to control hardware mirroring until it is decided whether to
permanently remove hardware mirroring support. See crbug.com/1161556 for
details.

Name: kEnableLauncherSearchNormalization
Documentation: Enables normalization of search results in the launcher.

Name: kEnableMachineLearningModelLoaderWebPlatformApi
Documentation:
Enables the Machine Learning Model Loader Web Platform API. Explainer:
https://github.com/webmachinelearning/model-loader/blob/main/explainer.md

Name: kEnableOpenInNewTabFromStartSurfaceFeed
Documentation:
Feature that causes the "open in new tab" menu item to appear on feed items
on Start Surface.

Name: kEnableOverwritingPlaceholderUsernames
Documentation:
Enables the overwriting of prefilled username fields if the server predicted
the field to contain a placeholder value.

Name: kEnablePasswordManagerWithinFencedFrame
Documentation:
By default, Password Manager is disabled in fenced frames for now.
TODO(crbug.com/1294378): Remove once launched.

Name: kEnablePasswordsAccountStorage
Documentation:
Enables a second, Gaia-account-scoped password store for users who are signed
in but not syncing.

Name: kEnablePenetratingImageSelection
Documentation:
Allow image context menu selections to penetrate through transparent
elements.

Name: kEnablePerfettoClientApiProducer
Documentation:
Controls whether trace points are implemented using Perfetto's client library
(enabled) or legacy TraceLog (disabled).

Name: kEnablePersistentFilesystemInIncognito
Documentation: Enables persistent Filesystem API in incognito mode.

Name: kEnableRemovingAllThirdPartyCookies
Documentation: Enable removal of all third-party cookies and site data.

Name: kEnableRestrictedWebApis
Documentation: Enable the restricted web APIs for high-trusted apps.

Name: kEnableSaveDataHeader
Documentation: Enable save-data header separately (without enabled data reduction service).

Name: kEnableServiceWorkersForChromeUntrusted
Documentation: Enables service workers on chrome-untrusted:// urls.

Name: kEnableSuggestedFiles
Documentation: Enables Drive file suggestions in the suggestion chips.

Name: kEnableSuggestedLocalFiles
Documentation: Enables local file suggestions in the suggestion chips.

Name: kEnableTLS13EarlyData
Documentation: Enables TLS 1.3 early data.

Name: kEnableTabMuting
Documentation: Enables user control over muting tab audio from the tab strip.

Name: kEnableUserCloudSigninRestrictionPolicyFetcher
Documentation:
Enable the UserCloudSigninRestrictionPolicyFetcher to get the
ManagedAccountsSigninRestriction policy for a dasher account.

Name: kEnableVkPipelineCache
Documentation: Enable persistent storage of VkPipelineCache data.

Name: kEnableWALModeByDefault
Documentation: Enable WAL mode for all SQLite databases.

Name: kEnableWebAppUninstallFromOsSettings
Documentation: Enable web app uninstallation from Windows settings or control panel.

Name: kEnableZeroStateAppsRanker
Documentation:
Enable a model that ranks zero-state apps search result.
TODO(crbug.com/989350): This flag can be removed once the
AppSearchResultRanker is removed. Same with the
AppSearchResultRankerPredictorName.

Name: kEnableZeroStateMixedTypesRanker
Documentation: Enable a model that ranks zero-state files and recent queries.

Name: kEncryptedClientHello
Documentation:
Enables the TLS Encrypted ClientHello feature.
https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/draft-ietf-tls-esni-13

Name: kEnforceFullDelegation
Documentation: Used to reject the apps with partial delegation.

Name: kEnhancedProtection
Documentation: Enables Enhanced Safe Browsing.

Name: kEnterpriseConnectorsEnabled
Documentation:
Controls whether the Enterprise Connectors policies should be read by
ConnectorsManager.

Name: kEnumerateDevicesHideDeviceIDs
Documentation:
If this feature is enabled and device permission is not granted by the user,
media-device enumeration will provide at most one device per type and the
device IDs will not be available.
TODO(crbug.com/1019176): remove the feature in M89.

Name: kEstablishGpuChannelAsync
Documentation:
Enables establishing the GPU channel asnchronously when requesting a new
layer tree frame sink.

Name: kEventPath
Documentation: Gates the non-standard API Event.path to help its deprecation and removal.

Name: kExcludeLowEntropyImagesFromLCP
Documentation:
Controls whether LCP calculations should exclude low-entropy images. If
enabled, then the associated parameter sets the cutoff, expressed as the
minimum number of bits of encoded image data used to encode each rendered
pixel. Note that this is not just pixels of decoded image data; the rendered
size includes any scaling applied by the rendering engine to display the
content.

Name: kExpectCTPruning
Documentation: Enables limiting the size of Expect-CT table.

Name: kExpectCTReporting
Documentation:
Enables Expect CT reporting, which sends reports for opted-in sites
that don't serve sufficient Certificate Transparency information.

Name: kExperimentalContentSecurityPolicyFeatures
Documentation:
Content counterpart of ExperimentalContentSecurityPolicyFeatures in
third_party/blink/renderer/platform/runtime_enabled_features.json5. Enables
experimental Content Security Policy features ('navigate-to' and
'prefetch-src').

Name: kExperimentalFlingAnimation
Documentation:
Enables the use of a touch fling curve that is based on the behavior of
native apps on Windows.

Name: kExperimentalKeywordMode
Documentation:
Please do not add more features to this "big blob" list.
Instead, use the categorized and alphabetized lists below this "big blob".
You can create a new category if none of the existing ones fit.

Name: kExplicitHighResolutionTimerWin
Documentation:
Under this feature, tasks that need high resolution timer are determined
based on explicit DelayPolicy rather than based on a threshold.

Name: kExplicitLanguageAsk
Documentation:
The feature that enables explicitly asking for user preferred
Accept-Languages on second run on Android. Replaced by kAppLanguagePrompt.

Name: kExposeSwDecodersToWebRTC
Documentation:
If enabled, when RTCVideoDecoderAdapter is used then SW decoders will be
exposed directly to WebRTC.

Name: kExtensionTelemetry
Documentation:
Enables collection of signals related to extension activity and uploads
of telemetry reports to SB servers.

Name: kExtensionTelemetryPersistence
Documentation:
Enables data collected by the kExtensionTelemetry to be written and read to
disk. This data will be uploaded for analysis.

Name: kExtensionTelemetryReportContactedHosts
Documentation: Enables reporting of remote hosts contacted by extensions in telemetry.

Name: kExtensionTelemetryTabsExecuteScriptSignal
Documentation:
Enables collection of telemetry signal whenever an extension invokes the
tabs.executeScript API call.

Name: kExtensionWorkflowJustification
Documentation:
Controls whether the user justification text field is visible on the
extension request dialog.

Name: kExternalClearKeyForTesting
Documentation:
Enables support for External Clear Key (ECK) key system for testing on
supported platforms. On platforms that do not support ECK, this feature has
no effect.

Name: kExternalExtensionDefaultButtonControl
Documentation:
If enabled, this feature's |kExternalInstallDefaultButtonKey| field trial
parameter value controls which |ExternalInstallBubbleAlert| button is the
default.

Name: kExtraCookieValidityChecks
Documentation:
When enabled, additional cookie-related APIs will perform cookie field size
and character set validation to enforce stricter conformance with RFC6265bis.
TODO(crbug.com/1243852) Eventually enable this permanently and remove the
feature flag, assuming no breakage occurs with it enabled.

Name: kExtraSafelistedRequestHeadersForOutOfBlinkCors
Documentation: Extra CORS safelisted headers. See https://crbug.com/999054.

Name: kEyeDropper
Documentation: Used to enable the eye-dropper in the refresh color-picker.

Name: kFFmpegDecodeOpaqueVP8
Documentation: Prefer FFmpeg to LibVPX for Vp8 decoding with opaque alpha mode.

Name: kFailUrlProvisionFetcherForTesting
Documentation:
Prevents UrlProvisionFetcher from making a provisioning request. If
specified, any provisioning request made will not be sent to the provisioning
server, and the response will indicate a failure to communicate with the
provisioning server.

Name: kFallbackAfterDecodeError
Documentation:
Falls back to other decoders after audio/video decode error happens. The
implementation may choose different strategies on when to fallback. See
DecoderStream for details. When disabled, playback will fail immediately
after a decode error happens. This can be useful in debugging and testing
because the behavior is simpler and more predictable.

Name: kFastSolidColorDraw
Documentation: Uses glClear to composite solid color quads whenever possible.

Name: kFasterSetCookie
Documentation:
Don't wait for database write before responding to
RestrictedCookieManager::SetCookieFromString.

Name: kFeatureNotificationGuide
Documentation: Main feature flag for the feature notification guide feature.

Name: kFedCm
Documentation:
Enables JavaScript API to intermediate federated identity requests.
Note that actual exposure of the FedCM API to web content is controlled
by the flag in RuntimeEnabledFeatures on the blink side. See also
the use of kSetOnlyIfOverridden in content/child/runtime_features.cc.
We enable it here by default to support use in origin trials.

Name: kFedCmManifestValidation
Documentation: Kill switch for FedCm manifest validation.

Name: kFeedBackToTop
Documentation:
Feature that enables showing a callout to help users return to the top of the
feeds quickly.

Name: kFeedClearImageMemoryCache
Documentation:
Feature that enables clearing the image memory cache when the feed is
destroyed.

Name: kFeedImageMemoryCacheSizePercentage
Documentation:
Feature that allows tuning the size of the image memory cache. Value is a
percentage of the maximum size calculated for the device.

Name: kFeedInteractiveRefresh
Documentation: Feature that enables refreshing feeds triggered by the users.

Name: kFeedLoadingPlaceholder
Documentation:
Feature that shows placeholder cards instead of a loading spinner at first
load.

Name: kFeedStamp
Documentation: Feature that enables StAMP cards in the feed.

Name: kFeedbackOnContinueSectionRemove
Documentation: Shows a feedback dialog when removing a continue section suggestion.

Name: kFencedFrames
Documentation:
Enable the <fencedframe> element; see crbug.com/1123606. Note that enabling
this feature does not automatically expose this element to the web, it only
allows the element to be enabled by the runtime enabled feature, for origin
trials.

Name: kFileHandlingAPI
Documentation: File handling integration. https://crbug.com/829689

Name: kFileHandlingIcons
Documentation: File handling icons. https://crbug.com/1218213

Name: kFileSystemAccessPersistentPermissions
Documentation: Enables persistent permissions for the File System Access API.

Name: kFileSystemConnectorEnabled
Documentation: Experimental flag to enable or disable the file system connector.

Name: kFileTypePoliciesTag
Documentation: Determines the tag to pass to Omaha to get a file type policy.

Name: kFillOnAccountSelect
Documentation:
Enables the experiment for the password manager to only fill on account
selection, rather than autofilling on page load, with highlighting of fields.

Name: kFillingAcrossAffiliatedWebsites
Documentation:
Enables filling password on a website when there is saved password on
affiliated website.

Name: kFilterAdsOnAbusiveSites
Documentation: Enables the blocking of ads on sites that are abusive.

Name: kFilteringScrollPrediction
Documentation:
Enables filtering of predicted scroll events on compositor thread.
Uses the kFilterName* values in ui_base_features.h as the 'filter' feature
param.

Name: kFirstPartySets
Documentation: Enables usage of First Party Sets to determine cookie availability.

Name: kFixedUmaSessionResumeOrder
Documentation: TODO(b/182286787): A/B experiment monitoring session/activity resume order.

Name: kFledge
Documentation: FLEDGE ad serving runtime flag/JS API.

Name: kFledgeLimitNumAuctions
Documentation:
If enabled, limits the number of FLEDGE auctions that can be run between page
load and unload -- any attempt to run more than this number of auctions will
fail (return null to JavaScript).

Name: kFocusFollowsCursor
Documentation: Enables focus follow follow cursor (sloppyfocus).

Name: kFontAccess
Documentation: Font enumeration and data access. https://crbug.com/535764

Name: kFontManagerEarlyInit
Documentation:
Whether to initialize the font manager when the renderer starts on a
background thread.

Name: kFontSrcLocalMatching
Documentation:
Enables fixes for matching src: local() for web fonts correctly against full
font name or postscript name. Rolling out behind a flag, as enabling this
enables a font indexer on Android which we need to test in the field first.

Name: kForceAppLanguagePrompt
Documentation: This feature forces the app UI prompt even if it has already been shown.

Name: kForceDisableExtendedSyncPromos
Documentation: This feature disables all extended sync promos.

Name: kForceEnablePasswordDomainCapabilities
Documentation:
Force enables password change capabilities for every domain, regardless of
the server response. The flag is meant for end-to-end testing purposes only.

Name: kForceFieldTrialSetupCrashForTesting
Documentation:
A testing feature that forces a crash during field trial creation
on developer and test builds.

Name: kForceHardwareAudioDecoders
Documentation:
Forces use of hardware (platform) audio decoders in
`media::DecoderSelector`.

Name: kForceHardwareVideoDecoders
Documentation:
Forces use of hardware (platform) video decoders in
`media::DecoderSelector`.

Name: kForceIsolationInfoFrameOriginToTopLevelFrame
Documentation:
Forces the `frame_origin` value in IsolationInfo to the `top_level_origin`
value when an IsolationInfo instance is created. This is to enable
expirimenting with double keyed network partitions.

Name: kForceMajorVersionInMinorPositionInUserAgent
Documentation:
If enabled, the major version number returned by Chrome will be locked at
99. The minor version number returned by Chrome will be forced to the
value of the major version number. The purpose of this
feature is a back up plan for if the major version moving from
two to three digits breaks unexpected things.

Name: kForceShowContinueSection
Documentation:
Forces the launcher to show the continue section even if there are no file
suggestions.

Name: kForceStartupSigninPromo
Documentation: Features to trigger the startup sign-in promo at boot.

Name: kForceWebContentsDarkMode
Documentation: Automatically convert light-themed pages to use a Blink-generated dark theme

Name: kForcedColors
Documentation: Used to enable forced colors mode for web content.

Name: kFractionalScrollOffsets
Documentation:
Enables scrollers inside Blink to store scroll offsets in fractional
floating-point numbers rather than truncating to integers.

Name: kFrameExperimentOnlyWhenLoading
Documentation:
Used along with |kLowPriorityForHiddenFrame|,
|kLowPriorityForSubFrameThrottleableTask|, |kLowPriorityForThrottleableTask|,
|kLowPriorityForSubFrame| to enable one of these experiments only during the
load use case.

Name: kFreezePurgeMemoryAllPagesFrozen
Documentation: Perform memory purges after freezing only if all pages are frozen.

Name: kFrequencyCappingForLargeStickyAdDetection
Documentation:
Enables the frequency capping for detecting large sticky ads.
Large-sticky-ads are those ads that stick to the bottom of the page
regardless of a user’s efforts to scroll, and take up more than 30% of the
screen’s real estate.

Name: kFrequencyCappingForOverlayPopupDetection
Documentation:
Enables the frequency capping for detecting overlay popups. Overlay-popups
are the interstitials that pop up and block the main content of the page.

Name: kFullUserAgent
Documentation:
Enables the `sec-ch-ua-full` client hint to be sent along with the full user
agent string in the HTTP request headers, as well as surfacing the full user
agent string in the JS APIs (navigator.userAgent, etc).

Name: kGPayAppDynamicUpdate
Documentation:
If enabled, the GooglePayPaymentApp handles communications between the native
GPay app and the browser for dynamic updates on shipping and payment data.

Name: kGWSPrefetchHoldback
Documentation: Preconnects instead of prefetching from GWS.

Name: kGav1VideoDecoder
Documentation: Use Gav1VideoDecoder to decode AV1 streams.

Name: kGenericSensorExtraClasses
Documentation:
The features should be documented alongside the definition of their values
in the .cc file.

Name: kGeoLanguage
Documentation:
Controls whether the GeoLanguage system is enabled. GeoLanguage uses IP-based
coarse geolocation to provide an estimate (for use by other Chrome features
such as Translate) of the local/regional language(s) corresponding to the
device's location. If this feature is disabled, the GeoLanguage provider is
not initialized at startup, and clients calling it will receive an empty list
of languages.

Name: kGiveJavaUiThreadDefaultTaskTraitsUserBlockingPriority
Documentation:
Gives Java tasks that are posted with the UiThreadTaskTraits.DEFAULT traits
user-blocking priority rather than their default user-visible priority.
See crbug.com/1259560.

Name: kGlobalMediaControls
Documentation: Show toolbar button that opens dialog for controlling media sessions.

Name: kGlobalMediaControlsAutoDismiss
Documentation: Auto-dismiss global media controls.

Name: kGlobalMediaControlsForChromeOS
Documentation: Allow Global Media Controls in system tray of CrOS.

Name: kGlobalMediaControlsModernUI
Documentation: Enable an updated version of the Global Media Controls UI.
AboutFlagOs: kOsWin | kOsMac | kOsLinux | kOsLacros | kOsCrOS | kOsFuchsia

Name: kGlobalMediaControlsPictureInPicture
Documentation: Show picture-in-picture button in Global Media Controls.

Name: kGlobalMediaControlsSeamlessTransfer
Documentation: Enable selection of audio output device in Global Media Controls.

Name: kGlobalVaapiLock
Documentation:
Enable global VA-API lock. Disable this to use lock-free VA-API function
calls for thread safe backends.

Name: kGpuUseDisplayThreadPriority
Documentation: Use ThreadPriority::DISPLAY for GPU main, viz compositor and IO threads.

Name: kGreaseUACH
Documentation:
Determines if an extra brand version pair containing possibly escaped double
quotes and escaped backslashed should be added to the Sec-CH-UA header
(activated by kUserAgentClientHint)

Name: kHTMLParamElementUrlSupport
Documentation:
TODO(crbug.com/1315717): This flag is being used to deprecate support for
<param> urls within <object> elements. This feature is controlled by
blink::features::kHTMLParamElementUrlSupport.

Name: kHardwareMediaKeyHandling
Documentation: Enables handling of hardware media keys for controlling media.

Name: kHardwareSecureDecryption
Documentation:
Enables hardware secure decryption if supported by hardware and CDM.
TODO(xhwang): Currently this is only used for development of new features.
Apply this to Android and ChromeOS as well where hardware secure decryption
is already available.

Name: kHardwareSecureDecryptionExperiment
Documentation:
Same as `kHardwareSecureDecryption` above, but only enable experimental
sub key systems. Which sub key system is experimental is key system specific.

Name: kHardwareSecureDecryptionFallback
Documentation:
Allows automatically disabling hardware secure Content Decryption Module
(CDM) after failures or crashes to fallback to software secure CDMs. If this
feature is disabled, the fallback will never happen and users could be stuck
in playback failures.

Name: kHeavyAdIntervention
Documentation:
Enables or disables the intervention that unloads ad iframes with intensive
resource usage.

Name: kHeavyAdInterventionWarning
Documentation:
Enables or disables reporting on the intervention that unloads ad iframes
with intensive resource usage.

Name: kHeavyAdPrivacyMitigations
Documentation:
Enables or disables the privacy mitigations for the heavy ad intervention.
This throttles the amount of interventions that can occur on a given host in
a time period. It also adds noise to the thresholds used. This is separate
from the intervention feature so it does not interfere with field trial
activation, as this blocklist is created for every user, and noise is decided
prior to seeing a heavy ad.

Name: kHidePrefetchParameter
Documentation:
This is a temporal flag added for supporting a workaround that allows
prerender2 to stop the location bar from the displaying prefetch flag, we
will turn if off after we confirm the prerendered document will handle it by
themselves.

Name: kHideWebAppOriginText
Documentation: Hides the origin text from showing up briefly in WebApp windows.

Name: kHighPriorityBeforeUnload
Documentation:
Tells the RenderFrameHost to send beforeunload messages on a different
local frame interface which will handle the messages at a higher priority.

Name: kHighPriorityDatabaseTaskType
Documentation: Enable setting high priority database task type from field trial parameters.

Name: kHistoryClustersInternalsPage
Documentation: Enables the history clusters internals page.

Name: kHistoryClustersUseContinueOnShutdown
Documentation: Enables use of task runner with trait CONTINUE_ON_SHUTDOWN.

Name: kHistoryQuickProviderAblateInMemoryURLIndexCacheFile
Documentation:
If enabled, the HistoryQuickProvider's InMemoryURLIndex service never
persists its index to a cache file on shutdown, and instead always rebuilds
it from the HistoryService on startup. Persisting the index to disk causes
over 10% of all shutdown hangs.

Name: kHlsPlayer
Documentation:
Enables the use of MediaPlayerRenderer for HLS playback. When disabled,
HLS manifests will fail to load (triggering source fallback or load error).

Name: kHttpsOnlyMode
Documentation: Sets whether the HTTPS-Only Mode setting is displayed in the settings UI.

Name: kHudDisplayForPerformanceMetrics
Documentation:
When enabled, cc will show blink's Web-Vital metrics inside its heads up
display.

Name: kIOSEnablePasswordManagerBrandingUpdate
Documentation:
Feature flag that updates icons, strings, and views for Google Password
Manager.

Name: kIOSSharedHighlightingV2
Documentation: Feature flag that enable Shared Highlighting V2 in iOS.

Name: kIPHDemoMode
Documentation: A feature for enabling a demonstration mode for In-Product Help (IPH).

Name: kIPHDummyFeature
Documentation: A feature to ensure all arrays can contain at least one feature.

Name: kIPHInWebUIDemo
Documentation: When enabled, shows a demo of in-product help in a WebUI context.

Name: kIPHSnooze
Documentation: A feature for enabling a snooze mode for In-Product Help (IPH).

Name: kIPv6Probing
Documentation: Enable IPv6 ping probes to RIPE DNS.

Name: kIdentifiabilityStudy
Documentation:
Root feature for all identifiability study logic.

If the feature is disabled, then this browser instance will not be
participating in the identifiability study. I.e. no identifiability metrics
will be recorded or reported.

Enabling the feature doesn't automatically make this client part of the study
either.

Name: kIdleDetection
Documentation:
This is intended as a kill switch for the Idle Detection feature. To enable
this feature, the experimental web platform features flag should be set,
or the site should obtain an Origin Trial token.

Name: kIgnoreSyncEncryptionKeysLongMissing
Documentation:
Causes Sync to ignore updates encrypted with keys that have been missing for
too long from this client; Sync will proceed normally as if those updates
didn't exist.

Name: kImageSearchSuggestionThumbnail
Documentation:
Feature to enable showing thumbnail in front of the Omnibox clipboard image
search suggestion.

Name: kImpulseScrollAnimations
Documentation:
Enables impulse-style scroll animations in place of the default ones.

Note: Do not enable this on the Mac. The animation does not match the system
scroll animation curve to such an extent that it makes Chromium stand out in
a bad way.

Name: kIncludeBackgroundSVGInLCP
Documentation: When enabled, this includes SVG background images in LCP calculation.

Name: kIncludeInitiallyInvisibleImagesInLCP
Documentation:
When enabled, this turns off an LCP calculation optimization that's ignoring
initially invisible images, and resulting in LCP correctness issues. See
https://crbug.com/1249622

Name: kIncludeIpcOverheadInNavigationStart
Documentation:
Historically most navigations required IPC from browser to renderer and
from renderer back to browser. This was done to check for before-unload
handlers on the current page and occurred regardless of whether a
before-unload handler was present. The navigation start time (as used in
various metrics) is the time the renderer initiates the IPC back to the
browser. If this feature is enabled, the navigation start time takes into
account the cost of the IPC from the browser to renderer. More specifically:
navigation_start = time_renderer_sends_ipc_to_browser -
   (time_renderer_receives_ipc - time_browser_sends_ipc)
Note that navigation_start does not take into account the amount of time the
renderer spends processing the IPC (that is, executing script).

Name: kIncognitoBrandConsistencyForAndroid
Documentation: When enabled, keeps Incognito UI consistent regardless of any selected theme.

Name: kIncognitoDownloadsWarning
Documentation: When enabled, users will see a warning when downloading from Incognito.

Name: kIncognitoFileSystemContextForTesting
Documentation:
Creates FileSystemContexts in incognito mode. This is used to run web tests
in incognito mode to ensure feature parity for FileSystemAccessAccessHandles.

Name: kIncognitoNtpRevamp
Documentation: When enabled, users will see updated UI in Incognito NTP

Name: kIncreaseBufferCountForHighFrameRate
Documentation: Increase number of buffers and pipeline depth for high frame rate devices.

Name: kInferConfirmationPasswordField
Documentation:
Enables finding a confirmation password field during saving by inspecting the
values of the fields. Used as a kill switch.
TODO(crbug.com/1164861): Remove once confirmed to be safe (around M92 or so).

Name: kInfoCardAcknowledgementTracking
Documentation: Feature that enables tracking the acknowledgement state for the info cards.

Name: kInitialNavigationEntry
Documentation:
Whether we will create initial NavigationEntry or not on FrameTree creation,
which also impacts the session history replacement decisions made in the
renderer.

Name: kInputMethodSettingsUiUpdate
Documentation:
Update of the virtual keyboard settings UI as described in
https://crbug.com/876901.

Name: kInputPredictorTypeChoice
Documentation:
This flag is used to set field parameters to choose predictor we use when
kResamplingInputEvents is disabled. It's used for gatherig accuracy metrics
on finch and also for choosing predictor type for predictedEvents API without
enabling resampling. It does not have any effect when the resampling flag is
enabled.

Name: kInputTargetClientHighPriority
Documentation:
Elevates the InputTargetClient mojo interface to input, since its input
blocking.

Name: kInstallableAmbientBadgeInfoBar
Documentation: Enables or disables the installable ambient badge infobar.

Name: kInstallableAmbientBadgeMessage
Documentation: Enables or disables the installable ambient badge message.

Name: kInstalledApp
Documentation: Kill switch for the GetInstalledRelatedApps API.

Name: kInstalledAppProvider
Documentation: Allow Windows specific implementation for the GetInstalledRelatedApps API.

Name: kInstalledAppsInCbd
Documentation:
Show warning about clearing data from installed apps in the clear browsing
data flow. The warning will be shown in a second dialog.

Name: kIntelVpSuperResolution
Documentation: Allow overlay swapchain to use Intel video processor for super resolution.

Name: kIntensiveWakeUpThrottling
Documentation:
When enabled, wake ups from throttleable TaskQueues are limited to 1 per
minute in a page that has been backgrounded for 5 minutes.

Intensive wake up throttling is enforced in addition to other throttling
mechanisms:
 - 1 wake up per second in a background page or hidden cross-origin frame
 - 1% CPU time in a page that has been backgrounded for 10 seconds

Feature tracking bug: https://crbug.com/1075553

The base::Feature should not be read from; rather the provided accessors
should be used, which also take into account the managed policy override of
the feature.

The base::Feature is enabled by default on all platforms. However, on
Android, it has no effect because page freezing kicks in at the same time. It
would have an effect if the grace period ("grace_period_seconds" param) was
reduced.

Name: kIntentBlockExternalFormRedirectsNoGesture
Documentation: Alphabetical:

Name: kInterestFeedSpinnerAlwaysAnimate
Documentation: Used for A:B testing of a bug fix (crbug.com/1151391).

removed.

click and view actions in the feed (e.g., the user needs to view X cards).

InterestFeedV2 is cached in ChromeCachedFlags. If the default value here is
changed, please update the cached one's default value in CachedFeatureFlags.

Name: kInterestGroupStorage
Documentation:
Main controls for ad serving API features.

Backend storage + kill switch for Interest Group API origin trials.

Name: kInternalMediaSession
Documentation:
Enables the internal Media Session logic without enabling the Media Session
service.

Name: kIsAblated
Documentation: Feature that when enabled completely removes all Feeds from chrome.

Name: kIsolateOrigins
Documentation:
Alternative to switches::kIsolateOrigins, for turning on origin isolation.
List of origins to isolate has to be specified via
kIsolateOriginsFieldTrialParamName.

Name: kIsolatePrerenders
Documentation:
Forces all eligible prerenders to be done in an isolated manner such that no
user-identifying information is used during the prefetch.

Name: kIsolatePrerendersMustProbeOrigin
Documentation: Forces Chrome to probe the origin before reusing a cached response.

Name: kIsolateSandboxedIframes
Documentation:
Allow process isolation of iframes with the 'sandbox' attribute set. Whether
or not such an iframe will be isolated may depend on options specified with
the attribute. Note: At present, only iframes with origin-restricted
sandboxes are isolated.

Name: kJXL
Documentation: Enables the JPEG XL Image File Format (JXL).

Name: kJankInjectionAblationFeature
Documentation: When enabled, some jank is injected to the animation/scrolling pipeline.

Name: kJourneys
Documentation:
Enables Journeys in the Chrome History WebUI. This flag shouldn't be checked
directly. Instead use `IsJourneysEnabled()` for the system language filter.

Name: kJourneysLabels
Documentation: Enables labelling of Journeys in UI.

Name: kKalmanDirectionCutOff
Documentation:
Enables discarding the prediction if the predicted direction is opposite from
the current direction.

Name: kKalmanHeuristics
Documentation: Enables changing the influence of acceleration based on change of direction.

Name: kKeepRvfcFrameAlive
Documentation:
Takes a reference on a video frame, keeping it alive during the duration of a
video.requestVideoFrameCallback call. Doesn't change anything to the API for
now, as this is only used to measure the potential impact of keeping frames
alive for longer. See crbug.com/1259784.

Name: kKeyPinningComponentUpdater
Documentation:
Controls whether the static key pinning list can be updated via component
updater.

Name: kKeyPressMonitoring
Documentation:
Keypress detection which serves as input to noise suppression methods
in WebRTC clients. This functionality is enabled by default but it can be
disabled experemantally by using --disable-features=KeyPressMonitoring.

Name: kKeyboardAccessibleTooltip
Documentation: Used to enable keyboard accessible tooltips.

Name: kLCPAnimatedImagesReporting
Documentation:
Enables reporting and web-exposure (respectively) of the time the first frame
of an animated image was painted.

Name: kLauncherGameSearch
Documentation: Enables cloud game search in the launcher.

Name: kLauncherLacrosIntegration
Documentation:
Forces the Launcher provider to send Omnibox search queries to the lacros
browser. If disabled, queries are sent to the ash browser.

Name: kLauncherPlayStoreSearch
Documentation: Enables Play Store search in the launcher.

Name: kLauncherSettingsSearch
Documentation: Enables launcher search results for OS settings.

Name: kLayoutNG
Documentation: Enable LayoutNG.

Name: kLayoutNGBlockInInline
Documentation: Enable by default. This feature is for a kill switch.

Name: kLazyInitializeMediaControls
Documentation: Enable lazy initialization of the media controls.

Name: kLeakDetectionUnauthenticated
Documentation: Enables password leak detection for unauthenticated users.

Name: kLegacyWindowsDWriteFontFallback
Documentation:
Configures whether Blink on Windows 8.0 and below should use out of process
API font fallback calls to retrieve a fallback font family name as opposed to
using a hard-coded font lookup table.

Name: kLensRegionSearch
Documentation: Enables Lens Region Search from the context menu.

Name: kLensStandalone
Documentation: Enables context menu search by image sending to the Lens homepage.

Name: kLightweightNoStatePrefetch
Documentation: A feature to reduce the set of resources fetched by No-State Prefetch.

Name: kLightweightReactions
Documentation: Main feature for the Lightweight Reactions project.

Name: kLimitAImageReaderMaxSizeToOne
Documentation:
Used to limit AImageReader max queue size to 1 since many devices especially
android Tv devices do not support more than 1 images.

Name: kLimitOpenUDPSockets
Documentation:
Enables a process-wide limit on "open" UDP sockets. See
udp_socket_global_limits.h for details on what constitutes an "open" socket.

Name: kListAllDisplayModes
Documentation:
This features allows listing all display modes of external displays in the
display settings and setting any one of them exactly as requested, which can
be very useful for debugging and development purposes.

Name: kLiveCaption
Documentation: Enables the Live Caption feature on supported devices.

Name: kLiveCaptionMultiLanguage
Documentation: Live Caption can be used in multiple languages, as opposed to just English.

Name: kLiveCaptionSystemWideOnChromeOS
Documentation: Live Caption runs system-wide on ChromeOS, as opposed to just in the browser.

Name: kLoadingPredictorUseLocalPredictions
Documentation:
All features in alphabetical order. The features should be documented
alongside the definition of their values in the .cc file.

Name: kLoadingTasksUnfreezable
Documentation:
Makes network loading tasks unfreezable so that they can be processed while
the page is frozen.

Name: kLocalHistorySuggestRevamp
Documentation:
Revamps how local search history is extracted and processed for generating
zero-prefix and prefix suggestions.

Name: kLocalHistoryZeroSuggest
Documentation: Allows the LocalHistoryZeroSuggestProvider to use local search history.

Name: kLogBreadcrumbs
Documentation: Feature flag to log breadcrumb events.

Name: kLogSplitDnsByNetworkIsolationKey
Documentation: Log dns requests by request

Name: kLogTLSResumption
Documentation: Log TLS resumption.

Name: kLoginDetection
Documentation: Enables login detection to sited based on various heuristics.

Name: kLoginEventReporting
Documentation:
Enable reporting Login events to the reporting connector when the Password
Manager detects that the user logged in to a web page.

Name: kLookalikeDigitalAssetLinks
Documentation: This feature enables Digital Asset Link validations for lookalikes.

Name: kLowDelayVideoRenderingOnLiveStream
Documentation: Enables low-delay video rendering in media pipeline on "live" stream.

Name: kLowLatencyCanvas2dImageChromium
Documentation:
Enables the use of GpuMemoryBuffer images for low latency 2d canvas.
TODO(khushalsagar): Enable this if we're using SurfaceControl and GMBs allow
us to overlay these resources.

Name: kLowLatencyCanvas2dSwapChain
Documentation: Enables the use of shared image swap chains for low latency 2d canvas.

Name: kLowLatencyWebGLSwapChain
Documentation: Enables the use of shared image swap chains for low latency webgl canvas.

Name: kLowPriorityForAdFrame
Documentation: Enables setting the priority of an ad frame to low priority.

Name: kLowPriorityForBackgroundPages
Documentation:
Enables setting the priority of background (with no audio) pages'
task queues to low priority.

Name: kLowPriorityForCrossOrigin
Documentation:
Enables setting the priority of cross-origin task queues to
low priority.

Name: kLowPriorityForCrossOriginOnlyWhenLoading
Documentation:
Enables setting the priority of cross-origin task queues to
low priority during loading only.

Name: kLowPriorityForHiddenFrame
Documentation:
Enables setting the priority of hidden frame task queues to
low priority.

Name: kLowPriorityForSubFrame
Documentation:
Enables setting the priority of sub-frame task queues to low
priority.

Name: kLowPriorityForSubFrameThrottleableTask
Documentation:
Enables setting the priority of sub-frame throttleable
task queues to low priority.

Name: kLowPriorityForThrottleableTask
Documentation:
Enables setting the priority of throttleable task queues to
low priority.

The MBI mode controls whether or not communication over the
AgentSchedulingGroup is ordered with respect to the render-process-global
legacy IPC channel, as well as the granularity of AgentSchedulingGroup
creation. This will break ordering guarantees between different agent
scheduling groups (ordering withing a group is still preserved).
DO NOT USE! The feature is not yet fully implemented. See crbug.com/1111231.

Name: kMacCoreLocationBackend
Documentation:
Enables usage of the CoreLocation API for LocationProvider instead of
NetworkLocationProvider for macOS.

Name: kManagedConfiguration
Documentation: Enables a Web API for websites to access admin-provided configuration.

Name: kMaxUnthrottledTimeoutNestingLevel
Documentation:
If enabled, the setTimeout(..., 0) will clamp to 4ms after a custom `nesting`
level.
Tracking bug: https://crbug.com/1108877.

Name: kMaxZeroSuggestMatches
Documentation:
Num suggestions - these affect how many suggestions are shown based on e.g.
focus, page context, provider, or URL v non-URL.

Name: kMayBlockWithoutDelay
Documentation:
Under this feature, workers blocked with MayBlock are replaced immediately
instead of waiting for a threshold in the foreground thread group.

Name: kMbiCompositorTaskRunnerPerAgentSchedulingGroup
Documentation:
If enabled, per-AgentGroupScheduler CompositorTaskRunner will be used instead
of per-MainThreadScheduler CompositorTaskRunner.

Name: kMbiOverrideTaskRunnerHandle
Documentation:
If enabled, base::ThreadTaskRunnerHandle::Get() and
base::SequencedTaskRunnerHandle::Get() returns the current active
per-ASG task runner instead of the per-thread task runner.

Name: kMdnsResponderGeneratedNameListing
Documentation:
If this feature is enabled, the mDNS responder service responds to queries
for TXT records associated with
"Generated-Names._mdns_name_generator._udp.local" with a list of generated
mDNS names (random UUIDs) in the TXT record data.

Name: kMediaCapabilitiesQueryGpuFactories
Documentation:
When enabled, MediaCapabilities will check with GPU Video Accelerator
Factories to determine isPowerEfficient = true/false.

Name: kMediaCapabilitiesWithParameters
Documentation: Enable Media Capabilities with finch-parameters.

Name: kMediaCastOverlayButton
Documentation: Display the Cast overlay button on the media controls.

Name: kMediaCodecHEVC
Documentation: Enables android HW decoding of HEVC content.

Name: kMediaControlsExpandGesture
Documentation:
Enable a gesture to make the media controls expaned into the display cutout.
TODO(beccahughes): Remove this.

If this feature is enabled, media-device enumerations use a cache that is
invalidated upon notifications sent by base::SystemMonitor. If disabled, the
cache is considered invalid on every enumeration request.

Name: kMediaDrmPersistentLicense
Documentation:
An experimental feature to enable persistent-license type support in MediaDrm
when using Encrypted Media Extensions (EME) API.
TODO(xhwang): Remove this after feature launch. See http://crbug.com/493521

MediaDrmBridge. If disabled, MediaDrmBridge will get unprovisioned origin IDs
which will trigger provisioning process after MediaDrmBridge is created.

Name: kMediaDrmPreprovisioningAtStartup
