Determines if MediaDrmOriginIdManager should attempt to pre-provision origin
IDs at startup (whenever a profile is loaded). Also used by tests that
disable it so that the tests can setup before pre-provisioning is done.
Note: Has no effect if kMediaDrmPreprovisioning feature is disabled.

Name: kMediaLearningExperiment
Documentation:
Enables experimental local learning for media. Used in the context of media
capabilities only. Adds reporting only; does not change media behavior.

Name: kMediaLearningFramework
Documentation:
Enables the general purpose media machine learning framework. Adds reporting
only; does not change media behavior.

Name: kMediaLearningSmoothnessExperiment
Documentation:
Enables the smoothness prediction experiment.  Requires
kMediaLearningFramework to be enabled also, else it does nothing.

Name: kMediaLicenseBackend
Documentation:
Use a custom backend to store media licenses in lieu of the
Plugin Private File System.

Name: kMediaOptimizer
Documentation:
Enable the prototype global optimization of tuneables via finch.  See
media/base/tuneable.h for how to create tuneable parameters.

Name: kMediaPowerExperiment
Documentation: Enable aggregate power measurement for media playback.

Name: kMediaSessionService
Documentation:
Enables the Media Session service including audio focus tracking. This allows
clients to consume the Media Session Mojo APIs but should not have any
changes to behavior. It is enabled by default on all platforms except Android.

Name: kMediaSessionWebRTC
Documentation: Enable WebRTC actions for the Media Session API.

Name: kMediaStreamTrackTransfer
Documentation: Allow cross-context transfer of MediaStreamTracks.

Name: kMediaStreamTrackUseConfigMaxFrameRate
Documentation:
Controls how max frame rates are enforced in MediaStreamTracks.
TODO(crbug.com/1152307): Remove in M91.

Name: kMemoryPressureBasedSourceBufferGC
Documentation:
Make MSE garbage collection algorithm more aggressive when we are under
moderate or critical memory pressure. This will relieve memory pressure by
releasing stale data from MSE buffers.

Name: kMessagesForAndroidAdsBlocked
Documentation:
Feature that controls whether "ads blocked" messages use Messages or
Infobars infrastructure.

Name: kMessagesForAndroidChromeSurvey
Documentation:
Feature that controls whether "survey" prompts use Messages or
Infobars infrastructure.

Name: kMessagesForAndroidInfrastructure
Documentation:
Feature that controls whether Messages for Android infrastucture components
are initialized. When this feature is disabled all individual message
implementations also fallback to Infobar implementations.

Name: kMessagesForAndroidInstantApps
Documentation:
Feature that controls whether "instant apps" messages use Messages or
Infobars infrastructure.

Name: kMessagesForAndroidNearOomReduction
Documentation:
Feature that controls whether "near OOM reduction" messages use Messages or
Infobars infrastructure.

Name: kMessagesForAndroidNotificationBlocked
Documentation:
Feature that controls whether notifiation blocked prompts use Messages or
Infobars infrastructure.

Name: kMessagesForAndroidOfferNotification
Documentation:
Feature that controls whether offer notifications use Messages or Infobars
infrastructure.

Name: kMessagesForAndroidPasswords
Documentation:
Feature that controls whether "save password" and "saved password
confirmation" prompts use Messages or Infobars infrastructure.

Name: kMessagesForAndroidPermissionUpdate
Documentation:
Feature that controls whether permission update prompts use Messages or
Infobars infrastructure.

Name: kMessagesForAndroidPopupBlocked
Documentation:
Feature that controls whether "popup blocked" prompts use Messages or
Infobars infrastructure.

Name: kMessagesForAndroidReaderMode
Documentation:
Feature that controls whether "reader mode" prompts use Messages or
Infobars infrastructure.

Name: kMessagesForAndroidReduceLayoutChanges
Documentation:
Feature that controls whether we always update layout parameters or only
while the message container is visible.

Name: kMessagesForAndroidSafetyTip
Documentation:
Feature that controls whether "safety tip" prompts use Messages or
Infobars infrastructure.

Name: kMessagesForAndroidSaveCard
Documentation:
Feature that controls whether "save card" prompts use Messages or
Infobars infrastructure.

Name: kMessagesForAndroidStackingAnimation
Documentation:
Feature that controls whether Messages for Android should use
new Stacking Animation.

Name: kMessagesForAndroidSyncError
Documentation:
Feature that controls whether "sync error" prompts use Messages or
Infobars infrastructure.

Name: kMessagesForAndroidUpdatePassword
Documentation:
Feature that controls whether "update password" prompt uses Messages or
Infobars infrastructure.

Name: kMetricsReportingFeature
Documentation: TODO(crbug.com/1068796): Replace kMetricsReportingFeature with a better name.

Name: kMetricsSettingsAndroid
Documentation: Enables the new design of metrics settings.

Name: kMigrateAlwaysTranslateLanguagesFix
Documentation:
Whether to migrate the obsolete always-translate languages pref to the new
pref during object construction as a fix for crbug/1291356, which had
previously not been migrated at all on iOS. This also enables a more
conservative pref merging process that aims to merge in old always-translate
language values from the obsolete pref without conflicting with any values in
the new pref that may have been added.

TODO(crbug/1291356): This base::Feature only exists to allow a less risky
merge into iOS M98. This base::Feature should be removed once it's no longer
relevant and the enabled behavior should become the only behavior.

Name: kMojoDedicatedThread
Documentation:
If enabled Mojo uses a dedicated background thread to listen for incoming
IPCs. Otherwise it's configured to use Content's IO thread for that purpose.

Name: kMojoRecordUnreadMessageCount
Documentation:
Enables measurement of MessageChannel unread message counts. When enabled, a
small random selection of Connectors enable the unread message count quota
on their associated message pipe, and record the highest unread message count
seen during the Connector's lifetime.

Name: kMojoVideoCapture
Documentation: Enables/disables the video capture service.

Name: kMojoVideoCaptureSecondary
Documentation:
A secondary switch used in combination with kMojoVideoCapture.
This is intended as a kill switch to allow disabling the service on
particular groups of devices even if they forcibly enable kMojoVideoCapture
via a command-line argument.

Name: kMostVisitedTiles
Documentation:
If enabled, frequently visited sites are presented in form of a single row
with a carousel of tiles, instead of one URL per row.

Name: kMouseSubframeNoImplicitCapture
Documentation: When enable, iframe does not implicit capture mouse event.

Name: kMultiPlaneVideoCaptureSharedImages
Documentation:
Enable binding multiple shared images to a single GpuMemoryBuffer for video
frames created by video capture.

Name: kMuteCompromisedPasswords
Documentation: Enables (un)muting compromised passwords from bulk leak check in settings.

Name: kNavigationNetworkResponseQueue
Documentation:
When NavigationNetworkResponseQueue is enabled, the browser will schedule
some tasks related to navigation network responses in a kHighest priority
queue.

Name: kNavigationPredictor
Documentation:
Used to control the collection of anchor element metrics (crbug.com/856683).
If kNavigationPredictor is enabled, then metrics of anchor elements
in the first viewport after the page load and the metrics of the clicked
anchor element will be extracted and recorded. Additionally, navigation
predictor may preconnect/prefetch to resources/origins to make the
future navigations faster.

Name: kNavigationPredictorEnablePreconnectOnSameDocumentNavigations
Documentation: Enables triggering of same-origin preconnects on same-document navigations.

Name: kNavigationPredictorPreconnectHoldback
Documentation:
All features in alphabetical order. The features should be documented
alongside the definition of their values in the .cc file.

Name: kNavigationPredictorPrefetchHoldback
Documentation: Preconnects instead of prefetching from NavigationPredictor.

Name: kNavigationRequestPreconnect
Documentation: Preconnects socket at the construction of NavigationRequest.

Name: kNavigationThreadingOptimizations
Documentation:
Enables optimizations for renderer->browser mojo calls to avoid waiting on
the UI thread during navigation.

Name: kNetUnusedIdleSocketTimeout
Documentation: Changes the timeout after which unused sockets idle sockets are cleaned up.

Name: kNetworkQualityEstimator
Documentation:
Enables optimizing the network quality estimation algorithms in network
quality estimator (NQE).

Name: kNetworkQualityEstimatorWebHoldback
Documentation:
Puts network quality estimate related Web APIs in the holdback mode. When the
holdback is enabled the related Web APIs return network quality estimate
set by the experiment (regardless of the actual quality).

Name: kNetworkServiceInProcess
Documentation: If the network service is enabled, runs it in process.

Name: kNetworkServiceSandbox
Documentation:
Enables network service sandbox.
(Only causes an effect when feature kNetworkService is enabled.)

Name: kNetworkTimeServiceQuerying
Documentation: Feature that enables network time service querying.

Name: kNewBrowsingContextStateOnBrowsingContextGroupSwap
Documentation:
Currently there are two paths - legacy code, in which BrowsingContextState
will be 1:1 with FrameTreeNode, allowing us to move proxy storage to it as a
no-op, and a new path hidden behind a feature flag, which will create a new
BrowsingContextState for cross-BrowsingInstance navigations.

Name: kNoForcedFrameUpdatesForWebTests
Documentation: Disables forced frame updates for web tests. Used by web test runner only.

Name: kNoReferrers
Documentation:
When kNoReferrers is enabled, most HTTP requests will provide empty
referrers instead of their ordinary behavior.

Name: kNonBlockingCommit
Documentation:
When enabled, the main thread does not block while commit is running on the
impl thread.
WARNING: This feature is not yet safe to enable. Work is needed to ensure
that main thread cc data structures are not modified on the main thread while
commit is running concurrently on the impl thread.

Name: kNonUniformityValidationFeature
Documentation:
Used to assess the reliability of field trial data by sending artificial
non-uniform data drawn from a log normal distribution.

Name: kNonUserVisibleDebug
Documentation:
Enables debug info in non-user-visible surfaces, like Chrome Inspector.
Does nothing if `kJourneys` is disabled.

Name: kNoncedPartitionedCookies
Documentation:
When enabled, then we allow partitioned cookies even if kPartitionedCookies
is disabled only if the cookie partition key contains a nonce. So far, this
is used to create temporary cookie jar partitions for fenced and anonymous
frames.

Name: kNotificationContentImage
Documentation: Kill switch for Web Notification content images.

Name: kNotificationScheduleService
Documentation: The feature to enable NotificationScheduleService.

Name: kNotificationTriggers
Documentation: Enables the notification trigger API.

Name: kNotifySyncOnLanguageDetermined
Documentation: Notify sync to update data on language determined.

Name: kNtlmV2Enabled
Documentation: Enables NTLMv2, which implicitly disables NTLMv1.

Name: kNtpMostLikelyFaviconsFromServerFeature
Documentation:
Feature to allow the new Google favicon server for fetching favicons for Most
Likely tiles on the New Tab Page.

Name: kNtpRealboxPedals
Documentation: Feature used to enable Pedals in the NTP Realbox.

Name: kNtpRealboxSuggestionAnswers
Documentation: Feature used to enable Suggestion Answers in the NTP Realbox.

Name: kNtpRealboxTailSuggest
Documentation: Feature used to enable Tail Suggest Formatting in the NTP Realbox.

Name: kNukeProfileBeforeCreateMultiAsync
Documentation:
Nukes profile directory before creating a new profile using
ProfileManager::CreateMultiProfileAsync().

Name: kObserverBasedPostProfileInit
Documentation:
Enables the use of a `ProfileManagerObserver` to trigger the post profile
init step of the browser startup. This affects the initialization order of
some features with the goal to improve startup performance in some cases.
See https://bit.ly/chromium-startup-no-guest-profile.

Name: kOffsetParentNewSpecBehavior
Documentation:
TODO(crbug.com/920069): Remove OffsetParentNewSpecBehavior after the feature
is in stable with no issues.

Name: kOmitCorsClientCert
Documentation:
Do not send TLS client certificates in CORS preflight. Omit all client certs
and continue the handshake without sending one if requested.

Name: kOmitNonUserGesturesFromReferrerChain
Documentation: Enable omitting non-user gesture from referrer chain.

Name: kOmniboxAction
Documentation:
Enables the Journeys Omnibox Action chip. `kJourneys` must also be enabled
for this to take effect.

Name: kOmniboxAssistantVoiceSearch
Documentation:
Omnibox UI - these affect the UI or function of the location bar (not the
popup).

Name: kOmniboxDemoteByType
Documentation:
Flags that affect the "twiddle" step of AutocompleteResult, i.e. SortAndCull.
TODO(tommycli): There are more flags above that belong in this category.

Name: kOmniboxExperimentalSuggestScoring
Documentation: Provider-specific - These features change the behavior of specific providers.

Name: kOmniboxFuzzyUrlSuggestions
Documentation: Feature used to enable URL suggestions for inputs that may contain typos.

Name: kOmniboxLocalZeroSuggestAgeThreshold
Documentation:
Used to adjust the age threshold since the last visit in order to consider a
normalized keyword search term as a zero-prefix suggestion. If disabled, the
default value of 60 days for Desktop and 7 days for Android and iOS is used.
If enabled, the age threshold is determined by this feature's companion
parameter, OmniboxFieldTrial::kOmniboxLocalZeroSuggestAgeThresholdParam.

Name: kOmniboxMaxURLMatches
Documentation:
Feature used to cap the number of URL-type matches shown within the
Omnibox. If enabled, the number of URL-type matches is limited (unless
there are no more non-URL matches available.) If enabled, there is a
companion parameter - OmniboxMaxURLMatches - which specifies the maximum
desired number of URL-type matches.

Name: kOmniboxPedalsAndroidBatch1
Documentation:
Feature used to enable the first batch of Pedals on Android. The Pedals,
which will be enabled on Android, should be already enabled on desktop.

Name: kOmniboxPedalsBatch3NonEnglish
Documentation:
Feature used to enable the third batch of Pedals (Find your phone, etc.)
for non-English locales (English locales are 'en' and 'en-GB').

Name: kOmniboxRemoveSuggestionsFromClipboard
Documentation: Feature used to allow users to remove suggestions from clipboard.

Name: kOmniboxSpareRenderer
Documentation: Spare renderer warmup for faster website loading.

Name: kOmniboxTrendingZeroPrefixSuggestionsOnNTP
Documentation:
Used to enable/disable remote zero-prefix suggestions on the NTP
(Omnibox and NTP realbox). Enabling this feature permits the code to issue
suggestions request to the server on the new tab page for users who decided
not to sign in.

Name: kOmniboxTriggerForNoStatePrefetch
Documentation:
Enables omnibox trigger no state prefetch. Only one of
kOmniboxTriggerForPrerender2 or kOmniboxTriggerForNoStatePrefetch can be
enabled in the experiment.
TODO(crbug.com/1267731): Remove this flag once the experiments are completed.

Name: kOmniboxTriggerForPrerender2
Documentation:
This flag is used for enabling Omnibox triggered prerendering and
blink::WebRuntimeFeatures::Prerender2RelatedFeatures that enables Prerender2
related web exposed features. This flag takes effect only when
blink::features::Prerender2 is enabled. See crbug.com/1166085 for more
details of Omnibox triggered prerendering.

Name: kOnDemandAccessibilityEvents
Documentation:
Allows the use of an experimental feature to drop any AccessibilityEvents
that are not relevant to currently enabled accessibility services.

Name: kOnDeviceClustering
Documentation: Enables configuring the on-device clustering backend.

Name: kOnDeviceClusteringBlocklists
Documentation: Specifies various blocklists for on-device clustering backend.

Name: kOnDeviceClusteringKeywordFiltering
Documentation: Specifies how keywords get filtered and added to a cluster.

Name: kOnDeviceHeadProviderIncognito
Documentation: On Device Head Suggest.

Name: kOnFocusSuggestionsContextualWeb
Documentation:
Enables on-focus suggestions on the Open Web, that are contextual to the
current URL. Will only work if user is signed-in and syncing, or is
otherwise eligible to send the current page URL to the suggest server.

There's multiple flags here for multiple backend configurations:
 - Default (search queries)
 - SRP specific toggle (enables SRP on top of Web Pages for features below)
 - On-Content Suggestions

TODO(tommycli): It's confusing whether Contextual Web includes SRP or not.
`kOnFocusSuggestionsContextualWebAllowSRP` suggests it's included, but
`kClobberTriggersContextualWebZeroSuggest` suggests it's not. Make this
consistent, probably by renaming flags to distinguish between OTHER and SRP.

Name: kOobeMarketingAdditionalCountriesSupported
Documentation: Enables/disables marketing emails for other countries other than US,CA,UK.

Name: kOobeMarketingDoubleOptInCountriesSupported
Documentation: Enables/disables marketing emails for double opt-in countries.

Name: kOomIntervention
Documentation: Enables or disabled the OOM intervention.

Name: kOpaqueResponseBlockingV01
Documentation:
Switches Cross-Origin Read Blocking (CORB) to use an early implementation of
Opaque Response Blocking (ORB, aka CORB++) behind the scenes.

This is ORB v0.1 - it doesn't implement the full spec from
https://github.com/annevk/orb:
- No Javascript sniffing is done.  Instead the implementation uses all
  of CORB's confirmation sniffers (for HTML, XML and JSON).
- Blocking is still done by injecting an empty response rather than erroring
  out the network request
- See other differences in the "ORB v0.1 vs full ORB differences" section in
  https://docs.google.com/document/d/1qUbE2ySi6av3arUEw5DNdFJIKKBbWGRGsXz_ew3S7HQ/edit#heading=h.mptmm5bpjtdn

Implementing ORB in Chromium is tracked in https://crbug.com/1178928

Name: kOptimizationGuideMetadataValidation
Documentation: Enables the validation of optimization guide metadata.

Name: kOptimizationGuideModelDownloading
Documentation: Enables the downloading of models.

Name: kOptimizationGuideUseContinueOnShutdownForPageContentAnnotations
Documentation:
Enables use of task runner with trait CONTINUE_ON_SHUTDOWN for page content
annotations on-device models.

Name: kOptimizationHints
Documentation: disabled by default

Name: kOptimizationHintsFieldTrials
Documentation:
Feature flag that contains a feature param that specifies the field trials
that are allowed to be sent up to the Optimization Guide Server.

Name: kOptimizationTargetPrediction
Documentation: Enables the prediction of optimization targets.

Name: kOptimizeDataUrls
Documentation: Alphabetical:

Name: kOptimizeEarlyNavigation
Documentation: Temporarily pauses the compositor early in navigation.

Name: kOptimizeNetworkBuffers
Documentation: Read as much of the net::URLRequest as there is space in the Mojo data pipe.

Name: kOptimizeViewportConstrainedPaintInvalidation
Documentation:
Removes a paint invalidation of viewport constrained objects (sticky or
fixed) after scrolling.

Name: kOriginAgentClusterDefaultEnabled
Documentation:
If enabled, an absent Origin-Agent-Cluster: header is interpreted as
requesting an origin agent cluster, but in the same process.

Name: kOriginAgentClusterDefaultWarning
Documentation:
This flag enables a console warning in cases where document.domain is set
without origin agent clustering being explicitly disabled.
(This is a transitory behaviour on the road to perma-enabling
kOriginAgentClusterDefaultEnabled above.)

Name: kOriginIsolationHeader
Documentation:
Controls the Origin-Agent-Cluster header. Tracking bug
https://crbug.com/1042415; flag removal bug (for when this is fully launched)
https://crbug.com/1148057.

The name is "OriginIsolationHeader" because that was the old name when the
feature was under development.

Name: kOriginPolicy
Documentation: Origin Policy. See https://crbug.com/751996

Name: kOriginTrialsSampleAPIThirdPartyAlternativeUsage
Documentation:
Sample field trial feature for testing alternative usage restriction in
origin trial third party tokens.

Name: kOverlayFullscreenVideo
Documentation: Only used for disabling overlay fullscreen (aka SurfaceView) in Clank.

Name: kOverlayScrollbar
Documentation:
Enables or disables overlay scrollbars in Blink (i.e. web content) on Aura
or Linux.  The status of native UI overlay scrollbars is determined in
PlatformStyle::CreateScrollBar. Does nothing on Mac.

Name: kOverrideTranslateTriggerInIndia
Documentation:
This feature controls the activation of the experiment to trigger Translate
in India on English pages independent of the user's UI language. The params
associated with the experiment dictate which model is used to determine the
target language.

Name: kOverscrollHistoryNavigation
Documentation: History navigation in response to horizontal overscroll (aka gesture-nav).

Name: kPageContentAnnotations
Documentation: Enables page content to be annotated.

Name: kPageEntitiesModelBypassFilters
Documentation:
This feature flag does not allow for the entities model to load the name and
prefix filters.

Name: kPageEntitiesModelResetOnShutdown
Documentation: This feature flag enables resetting the entities model on shutdown.

Name: kPageEntitiesPageContentAnnotations
Documentation: Enables the page entities model to be annotated on every page load.

Name: kPageInfoAboutThisSiteMoreInfo
Documentation: Shows a link with more info about a site in PageInfo.

Name: kPageInfoAboutThisSiteUrlGranularity
Documentation:
Switches from Host-level granularity to URL-level granularity.
Used by OptimizationGuide.

Name: kPageInfoDiscoverability
Documentation:
Used to experiment with different permission timeouts. The underlying feature
itself is already launched.

Name: kPageInfoHistory
Documentation: Enables the history sub page for Page Info.

Name: kPageInfoStoreInfo
Documentation: Enables the store info row for Page Info.

Name: kPageTextExtraction
Documentation:
This feature flag does not turn off any behavior, it is only used for
experiment parameters.

Name: kPageVisibilityPageContentAnnotations
Documentation: Enables the page visibility model to be annotated on every page load.

Name: kPaintHolding
Documentation:
Enable defer commits to avoid flash of unstyled content, for same origin
navigation only.

Name: kPaintHoldingCrossOrigin
Documentation: Enable defer commits to avoid flash of unstyled content, for all navigation.

Name: kPaintPreviewDemo
Documentation:
Used to enable a main menu item on Android that captures and displays a paint
preview for the current page. The paint preview UI will be dismissed on back
press and all associated stored files deleted. This intended to test whether
capturing and playing paint preview works on a specific site.

Name: kPaintPreviewShowOnStartup
Documentation:
Used to enable the paint preview capture and show on startup for Android. If
enabled, paint previews for each tab are captured when a tab is hidden and
are deleted when a tab is closed. When a tab with a captured paint perview
is shown at startup and there is no cached page we will show the paint
preview.

Name: kParakeet
Documentation: PARAKEET ad serving runtime flag/JS API.

Name: kParallelDownloading
Documentation: Whether a download can be handled by parallel jobs.

Name: kPartitionConnectionsByNetworkIsolationKey
Documentation:
Partitions connections based on the NetworkIsolationKey associated with a
request.

Name: kPartitionDomainReliabilityByNetworkIsolationKey
Documentation: Partitions Domain Reliability beacons and upload by NetworkIsolationKey.

Name: kPartitionExpectCTStateByNetworkIsolationKey
Documentation:
Partitions Expect-CT data by NetworkIsolationKey. This only affects the
Expect-CT data itself. Regardless of this value, reports will be uploaded
using the associated NetworkIsolationKey, when one's available.

This feature requires kPartitionConnectionsByNetworkIsolationKey,
kPartitionHttpServerPropertiesByNetworkIsolationKey, and
kPartitionConnectionsByNetworkIsolationKey to all be enabled to work.

Name: kPartitionHttpServerPropertiesByNetworkIsolationKey
Documentation:
Partitions HttpServerProperties based on the NetworkIsolationKey associated
with a request.

Name: kPartitionNelAndReportingByNetworkIsolationKey
Documentation:
Partitions Network Error Logging and Reporting API data by
NetworkIsolationKey. Also partitions all reports generated by other consumers
of the reporting API. Applies the NetworkIsolationKey to reports uploads as
well.

When disabled, the main entry points of the reporting and NEL services ignore
NetworkIsolationKey parameters, and they're cleared while loading from the
cache, but internal objects can be created with them (e.g., endpoints), for
testing.

Name: kPartitionSSLSessionsByNetworkIsolationKey
Documentation:
Partitions TLS sessions and QUIC server configs based on the
NetworkIsolationKey associated with a request.

This feature requires kPartitionConnectionsByNetworkIsolationKey to be
enabled to work.

Name: kPartitionedCookies
Documentation:
When enabled, sites can opt-in to having their cookies partitioned by
top-level site with the Partitioned attribute. Partitioned cookies will only
be sent when the browser is on the same top-level site that it was on when
the cookie was set.

Name: kPartitionedCookiesBypassOriginTrial
Documentation:
Flag to bypass the origin trial opt-in to use Partitioned cookies. This
allows developers to test Partitioned cookies manually in development
environments.
TODO(crbug.com/1296161): Remove this feature when the CHIPS OT ends.

Name: kPasswordBreachEventReporting
Documentation:
Enable reporting password leaks to the reporting connector when the Password
Manager's Leak Detector has found some compromised credentials.

Name: kPasswordChange
Documentation: Enables automatic password change flow from leaked password dialog.

Name: kPasswordChangeInSettings
Documentation: Enables password change flow from bulk leak check in settings.

Name: kPasswordChangeWellKnown
Documentation: Enables .well-known based password change flow from leaked password dialog.

Name: kPasswordDomainCapabilitiesFetching
Documentation:
Enables fetching credentials capabilities from server for the
|PasswordChangeInSettings| and |PasswordChange| features.

Name: kPasswordImport
Documentation: Controls the ability to import passwords from Chrome's settings page.

Name: kPasswordNotes
Documentation: Enables adding, displaying and modifying extra notes to stored credentials.

Name: kPasswordReuseDetectionEnabled
Documentation: Enables password reuse detection.

Name: kPasswordScriptsFetching
Documentation: Enables password scripts fetching for the |PasswordChangeInSettings| feature.

Name: kPasswordsAccountStorageRevisedOptInFlow
Documentation: Enables a revised opt-in flow for the account-scoped password storage.

Name: kPath2DPaintCache
Documentation:
Enables the use of the PaintCache for Path2D objects that are rasterized
out of process.  Has no effect when kCanvasOopRasterization is disabled.

Name: kPauseBrowserInitiatedHeavyTrafficForP2P
Documentation:
When kPauseBrowserInitiatedHeavyTrafficForP2P is enabled, then a subset of
the browser initiated traffic may be paused if there is at least one active
P2P connection and the network is estimated to be congested. This feature is
intended to throttle only the browser initiated traffic that is expected to
be heavy (has large request/response sizes) when real time content might be
streaming over an active P2P connection.

Name: kPaymentHandlerPopUpSizeWindow
Documentation:
Desktop only, if enabled payment handler window size matches the pop up
window size.

Name: kPaymentRequestBasicCard
Documentation:
Enable the basic-card payment method from the PaymentRequest API. This flag
will be used to deprecate basic-card eventually: crbug.com/1209835.

Name: kPepper3DImageChromium
Documentation:
If Pepper 3D Image Chromium is allowed, this feature controls whether it is
enabled.
TODO(https://crbug.com/1196009): Remove this feature, remove the code that
uses it.

Name: kPepperCrossOriginRedirectRestriction
Documentation: Kill-switch to introduce a compatibility breaking restriction.

Name: kPercentBasedScrolling
Documentation:
Enables percent-based scrolling for mousewheel and keyboard initiated
scrolls.

Name: kPerformanceHintsObserver
Documentation: Exposed for testing.

Name: kPeriodicBackgroundSync
Documentation: Whether web apps can run periodic tasks upon network connectivity.

Name: kPermissionAuditing
Documentation:
Keep a client-side log of when websites access permission-gated capabilities
to allow the user to audit usage.

Name: kPermissionChip
Documentation:
Enables an experimental permission prompt that uses a chip in the location
bar.

Name: kPermissionChipGestureSensitive
Documentation:
When kPermissionChip (above) is enabled, controls whether or not the
permission chip should be more prominent when the request is associated with
a gesture. Does nothing when kPermissionChip is disabled.

Name: kPermissionChipIsProminentStyle
Documentation:
When kPermissionChip (above) is enabled, controls whether or not the
permission chip should be shown in the prominent style (white on blue) or in
the secondary style (blue on white).

Name: kPermissionChipRequestTypeSensitive
Documentation:
When kPermissionChip (above) is enabled, controls whether or not the
permission chip should be more or less prominent depending on the request
type. Does nothing when kPermissionChip is disabled.

Name: kPermissionGeolocationPredictions
Documentation: Enables using the prediction service for geolocation permission prompts.

Name: kPermissionPredictionServiceUseUrlOverride
Documentation:
When enabled, use the value of the `service_url` FeatureParam as the url
for the Web Permission Predictions Service.

Name: kPermissionPredictions
Documentation:
Enables using the prediction service for permission prompts. We will keep
this feature in order to allow us to update the holdback chance via finch.

Name: kPermissionQuietChip
Documentation:
Enables an experimental less prominent permission prompt that uses a chip in
the location bar. Requires chrome://flags/#quiet-notification-prompts to be
enabled.

Name: kPermuteTLSExtensions
Documentation:
Enables permuting TLS extensions in the ClientHello, to reduce the risk of
non-compliant servers ossifying parts of the ClientHello and interfering with
deployment of future security improvements.

Name: kPersistContextAnnotationsInHistoryDb
Documentation:
This flag is to enable us to turn on persisting context annotations WITHOUT
exposing the Memories UI in general. If EITHER this flag or `kJourneys` is
enabled, users will have context annotations persisted into their History DB.

Name: kPersistentHistogramsFeature
Documentation: Feature definition for enabling histogram persistence.

Name: kPersistentQuotaIsTemporaryQuota
Documentation: Makes Persistent quota the same as Temporary quota.

Name: kPersonalizeFeedUnsignedUsers
Documentation: Personalize feed for unsigned users.

Name: kPervasivePayloadsList
Documentation: Load Pervasive Payloads List for Cache Transparency.

Name: kPictureInPicture
Documentation: Enable Picture-in-Picture.

Name: kPictureInPictureAPI
Documentation: Enable picture in picture web api for android.

Name: kPictureInPictureV2
Documentation:
A browser-side equivalent of the Blink feature "PictureInPictureV2". This is
used for sanity checks to ensure that the feature can't be enabled by a
compromised renderer despite the Blink flag not being enabled.

Name: kPlatformAudioEncoder
Documentation: Allows usage of OS-level (platform) audio encoders.

Name: kPlaybackSpeedButton
Documentation: Display the playback speed button on the media controls.

Name: kPlzDedicatedWorker
Documentation:
Enable browser-initiated dedicated worker script loading
(PlzDedicatedWorker). https://crbug.com/906991

Name: kPointerLockOptions
Documentation: Allows requesting unadjusted movement when entering pointerlock.

Name: kPopularSitesBakedInContentFeature
Documentation:
This feature is enabled by default. Otherwise, users who need it would not
get the right configuration timely enough. The configuration affects only
Android or iOS users.

Name: kPortals
Documentation:
Enable Portals. https://crbug.com/865123.
Note that default enabling this does not expose the portal
element on its own, but does allow its use with an origin trial. This was the
case for the M85 Android only origin trial (https://crbug.com/1040212).

Name: kPortalsCrossOrigin
Documentation:
When kPortals is enabled, allow portals to load content that is third-party
(cross-origin) to the hosting page. Otherwise has no effect.

https://crbug.com/1013389

Name: kPostQuantumCECPQ2
Documentation: Enables CECPQ2, a post-quantum key-agreement, in TLS 1.3 connections.

Name: kPostQuantumCECPQ2SomeDomains
Documentation:
Enables CECPQ2, a post-quantum key-agreement, in TLS 1.3 connections for a
subset of domains. (This is intended as Finch kill-switch. For testing
compatibility with large ClientHello messages, use |kPostQuantumCECPQ2|.)

Name: kPreconnectToSearch
Documentation: Feature to control preconnect to search.

Name: kPredictivePrefetchingAllowedOnAllConnectionTypes
Documentation: Allows prediction operations (e.g., prefetching) on all connection types.

Name: kPreemptiveLinkToTextGeneration
Documentation: Enables link to text to be generated in advance.

Name: kPreferCompositingToLCDText
Documentation:
Whether we should composite a PLSA (paint layer scrollable area) even if it
means losing lcd text.

Name: kPreferNewContentForCheckerboardedScrolls
Documentation:
When enabled, scheduler tree priority will change to
NEW_CONTENT_TAKES_PRIORITY if during a scrollbar scroll, CC has to
checkerboard.

Name: kPrefersColorSchemeClientHintHeader
Documentation: Handle prefers-color-scheme user preference media feature via client hints.

Name: kPrefetchAndroidFonts
Documentation: Enables prefetching Android fonts on renderer startup.

Name: kPrefetchPrivacyChanges
Documentation:
Prefetch request properties are updated to be privacy-preserving. See
crbug.com/988956.

Name: kPrefetchUseContentRefactor
Documentation:
If enabled, then prefetch requests from speculation rules should use the code
in content/browser/speculation_rules/prefetch/ instead of
chrome/browser/prefetch/prefetch_proxy/.

Name: kPreloadCookies
Documentation: Preload cookie database on NetworkContext creation.

Name: kPreloadMetadataLazyLoad
Documentation:
Only decode preload=metadata elements upon visibility.
TODO(crbug.com/879406): Remove this after M76 ships to stable

Name: kPrerender2
Documentation:
Prerender2:
Enables the Prerender2 feature: https://crbug.com/1126305
But see comments in the .cc file also.

Name: kPrerender2MemoryControls
Documentation:
Enables restrictions on how much memory is required on a device to use
Prerender2. This is a separate feature from kPrerender2 so that the
restrictions can be disabled entirely to allow bots to run the tests without
needing to explicitly enable Prerender2, which some tests do not want to do
because they want to test the default behavior.

Name: kPrerenderFallbackToPreconnect
Documentation: Allows Chrome to do preconnect when prerender fails.

Name: kPreviewsResourceLoadingHintsSpecificResourceTypes
Documentation: Enable limiting previews loading hints to specific resource types.

Name: kPrioritizeCompositingAfterInput
Documentation: Prioritizes one BeginMainFrame after input.

Name: kPrioritizeCompositingAndLoadingDuringEarlyLoading
Documentation: Prioritizes loading and compositing tasks while loading.

Name: kPrivacySandboxAdsAPIsOverride
Documentation:
Enables exposure of ads APIs in the renderer: Attribution Reporting,
FLEDGE, Topics.

Name: kPrivacySandboxAggregationService
Documentation: Enables the Aggregation Service. See crbug.com/1207974.

Name: kPrivacySandboxSettings3
Documentation: Enables the third release of the Privacy Sandbox settings.

Name: kPrivateNetworkAccessForWorkers
Documentation:
Enables Private Network Access checks for all types of web workers.

This affects initial worker script fetches, fetches initiated by workers
themselves, and service worker update fetches.

The exact checks run are the same as for other document subresources, and
depend on the state of other Private Network Access feature flags:

 - `kBlockInsecurePrivateNetworkRequests`
 - `kPrivateNetworkAccessSendPreflights`
 - `kPrivateNetworkAccessRespectPreflightResults`

Name: kPrivateNetworkAccessRespectPreflightResults
Documentation:
Requires that CORS preflight requests succeed before sending private network
requests. This flag implies `kPrivateNetworkAccessSendPreflights`.
See: https://wicg.github.io/private-network-access/#cors-preflight

Name: kPrivateNetworkAccessSendPreflights
Documentation:
Enables sending CORS preflight requests ahead of private network requests.
See: https://wicg.github.io/private-network-access/#cors-preflight

Name: kProactivelySwapBrowsingInstance
Documentation:
Enable the ProactivelySwapBrowsingInstance experiment. A browsing instance
represents a set of frames that can script each other. Currently, Chrome does
not always switch BrowsingInstance when navigating in between two unrelated
pages. This experiment makes Chrome swap BrowsingInstances for cross-site
HTTP(S) navigations when the BrowsingInstance doesn't contain any other
windows.

Name: kProactivelyThrottleLowPriorityRequests
Documentation:
When kProactivelyThrottleLowPriorityRequests is enabled,
resource scheduler proactively throttles low priority requests to avoid
network contention with high priority requests that may arrive soon.

Name: kProcessGaiaRemoveLocalAccountHeader
Documentation:
Enables the client-side processing of the HTTP response header
Google-Accounts-RemoveLocalAccount.

Name: kProcessSharingWithDefaultSiteInstances
Documentation:
Enables process sharing for sites that do not require a dedicated process
by using a default SiteInstance. Default SiteInstances will only be used
on platforms that do not use full site isolation.
Note: This feature is mutally exclusive with
kProcessSharingWithStrictSiteInstances. Only one of these should be enabled
at a time.

Name: kProcessSharingWithStrictSiteInstances
Documentation:
Whether cross-site frames should get their own SiteInstance even when
strict site isolation is disabled. These SiteInstances will still be
grouped into a shared default process based on BrowsingInstance.

Name: kPromoBrowserCommands
Documentation: Enables executing the browser commands sent by the NTP promos.

Name: kPseudoMetricsEffectFeature
Documentation:
Used to assess the reliability of field trial data by injecting different
levels of effects to pseudo metrics. These pseudo metrics are just mirrors of
some existing metrics.

Name: kPurgeRendererMemoryWhenBackgrounded
Documentation:
Perform a memory purge after a renderer is backgrounded. Formerly labelled as
the "PurgeAndSuspend" experiment.

TODO(https://crbug.com/926186): Disabled by default on Android for historical
reasons. Consider enabling by default if experiment results are positive.

Name: kPushMessagingBackgroundMode
Documentation:
Enables or disables push subscriptions keeping Chrome running in the
background when closed.

Name: kPushMessagingDisallowSenderIDs
Documentation: Feature flag to disallow creation of push messages with GCM Sender IDs.

Name: kPushNotifications
Documentation: Enables push notification of hints.

Name: kPushSubscriptionChangeEvent
Documentation:
Fires the `pushsubscriptionchange` event defined here:
https://w3c.github.io/push-api/#the-pushsubscriptionchange-event
for subscription refreshes, revoked permissions or subscription losses

Name: kPushSubscriptionWithExpirationTime
Documentation:
Feature flag to enable push subscription with expiration times specified in
/chrome/browser/push_messaging/push_messaging_constants.h

Name: kPwaUpdateDialogForIcon
Documentation: Shows a confirmation dialog when updates to a PWAs icon has been detected.

Name: kPwaUpdateDialogForName
Documentation: Shows a confirmation dialog when updates to a PWAs name has been detected.

Name: kQueryTiles
Documentation:
Main feature flag for the query tiles feature. All other flags are
effective only when this flag is enabled.

Name: kQueryTilesDisableCountryOverride
Documentation: Whether to disable the override rules introduced for countries.

Name: kQueryTilesEnableQueryEditing
Documentation:
Feature flag to determine whether the user will have a chance to edit the
query before in the omnibox sumbitting the search. In this mode only one
level of tiles will be displayed.

Name: kQueryTilesInNTP
Documentation: Feature flag to determine whether query tiles should be shown on NTP.

Name: kQueryTilesRemoveTrendingTilesAfterInactivity
Documentation:
Feature flag to determine whether trending tiles should disapear after
some time of inactivity.

Name: kQueryTilesSegmentation
Documentation: Whether segmentation rules are applied to query tiles.

Name: kQuickIntensiveWakeUpThrottlingAfterLoading
Documentation:
If enabled, the grace period of features::kIntensiveWakeUpThrottling will be
|kIntensiveWakeUpThrottling_GracePeriodSeconds_Loaded| when a background page
is loaded.

Name: kQuickUnlockPinAutosubmitBackfill
Documentation:

backfilled.

Name: kQuietNotificationPrompts
Documentation: Enables using quiet prompts for notification permission requests.

Name: kRTCGpuCodecSupportWaiter
Documentation:
Enables waiting for codec support status notification from GPU factory in RTC
codec factories.

Name: kRTCOfferExtmapAllowMixed
Documentation:
Determines if the SDP attrbute extmap-allow-mixed should be offered by
default or not. The default value can be overridden by passing
{offerExtmapAllowMixed:false} as an argument to the RTCPeerConnection
constructor.

Name: kRTCUnifiedPlanByDefault
Documentation:
Changes the default RTCPeerConnection constructor behavior to use Unified
Plan as the SDP semantics. When the feature is enabled, Unified Plan is used
unless the default is overridden (by passing {sdpSemantics:'plan-b'} as the
argument). This was shipped in M72.
The feature is still used by virtual test suites exercising Plan B.

Name: kRawDraw
Documentation: Enables Raw Draw.

Name: kReadLater
Documentation: Feature flag used for enabling Read later on desktop and Android.

Name: kReadLaterBackendMigration
Documentation:
Feature flag used for enabling the reading list backend migration.
When enabled, reading list data will also be stored in the Bookmarks backend.
This allows each platform to migrate their reading list front end to point at
the new reading list data stored in the bookmarks backend without
interruption to cross device sync if some syncing devices are on versions
with the migration behavior while others aren't. See crbug/1234426 for more
details.

Name: kReadLaterReminderNotification
Documentation: Feature flag used for enabling read later reminder notification.

Name: kRecordBackForwardCacheMetricsWithoutEnabling
Documentation:
This feature is used to limit the scope of back-forward cache experiment
without enabling it. To control the URLs list by using this feature by
generating the metrics only for "allowed_websites" param. Mainly, to ensure
that metrics from the control and experiment groups are consistent.

Name: kRecordMediaEngagementScores
Documentation:
Enables Media Engagement Index recording. This data will be used to determine
when to bypass autoplay policies. This is recorded on all platforms.

Name: kRecordRadioWakeupTrigger
Documentation:
Enable recording UMAs for network activities which can wake-up radio on
Android.

Name: kRecordWebAppDebugInfo
Documentation:
Enables recording additional web app related debugging data to be displayed
in: chrome://web-app-internals

Name: kRecordWebAudioEngagement
Documentation: Enables Media Engagement Index recording for Web Audio playbacks.

Name: kRecoverFromNeverSaveAndroid
Documentation:
Enables showing UI which allows users to easily revert their choice to
never save passwords on a certain website.

Name: kReduceHorizontalFlingVelocity
Documentation:
Reduces the velocity of horizontal flings. This is an experiment to test
a simple means of making flings in mandatory scroll snap areas feel more
natural. See https://crbug.com/1189696 for details.

Name: kReduceOpsTaskSplitting
Documentation: Enable Skia reduceOpsTaskSplitting to reduce render passes.

Name: kReduceUserAgent
Documentation: Freezes the user-agent as part of https://github.com/WICG/ua-client-hints.

Name: kReduceUserAgentMinorVersion
Documentation: If enabled, the minor version of the User-Agent string will be reduced.

Name: kReducedReferrerGranularity
Documentation:
Reduce the amount of information in the default 'referer' header for
cross-origin requests.

Name: kRefreshExpirationDate
Documentation: Whether download expiration date will be refreshed on resumption.

Name: kReliabilityLogging
Documentation: Whether to log reliability events.

Name: kReloadHiddenTabsWithCrashedSubframes
Documentation:
Causes hidden tabs with crashed subframes to be marked for reload, meaning
that if a user later switches to that tab, the current page will be
reloaded.  This will hide crashed subframes from the user at the cost of
extra reloads.

Name: kRemoteOptimizationGuideFetching

Name: kRemoveCanceledTasksInTaskQueue
Documentation: Controls whether or not canceled delayed tasks are removed from task queues.

Name: kRemoveMobileViewportDoubleTap
Documentation:
When enabled, the double tap to zoom will be disabled when the viewport
meta tag is properly set for mobile using content=width=device-width
or content=initial-scale=1.0

Name: kRenderAccessibilityHostDeserializationOffMainThread
Documentation:
Causes RenderAccessibilityHost messages to be handled initially on a thread
pool before being forwarded to the browser main thread to avoid so the
deserialization does not block it.

Name: kReportAssistedQueryStats

If enabled, we only report FCP if there’s a successful commit to the
compositor. Otherwise, FCP may be reported if first BeginMainFrame results in
a commit failure (see crbug.com/1257607).

Name: kReportOmniboxOnDeviceSuggestionsHeader
Documentation:
Whether to enable reporting the header. Included as a quick escape hatch in
case of crashes.

Name: kReportSearchboxStats
Documentation:
If enabled, Omnibox reports the Searchbox Stats in the gs_lcrp= param in the
Search Results Page URL.

Name: kRequestDesktopSiteExceptions
Documentation:
Request Desktop Site per-site setting for Android.
Refer to the launch bug (https://crbug.com/1244979) for more information.

Name: kRequestDesktopSiteGlobal

Name: kRequestSystemAudioFocus
Documentation:
When enabled, Playing media sessions will request audio focus from the
Android system.

Name: kRequireHdcpKeyProvisioning
Documentation:

kernel doesn't expose that it requires this yet.(b/112172923)

Name: kResamplingInputEvents
Documentation: Enables resampling input events on main thread.

Name: kResamplingScrollEvents
Documentation:
Enables resampling GestureScroll events on compositor thread.
Uses the kPredictorName* values in ui_base_features.h as the 'predictor'
feature param.

Name: kResamplingScrollEventsExperimentalPrediction
Documentation:
Enables resampling of scroll events using an experimental latency of +3.3ms
instead of the original -5ms.

Name: kResolutionBasedDecoderPriority
Documentation:
Enables a platform-specific resolution cutoff for prioritizing platform
decoders over software decoders or vice-versa.

Name: kRestartNetworkServiceUnsandboxedForFailedLaunch
Documentation:
When this feature is enabled, the network service will restart unsandboxed if
a previous attempt to launch it sandboxed failed.

Name: kRestrictGoogleWebVisibility
Documentation:
A feature that supports more finely-grained control over the transmission of
VariationIDs to Google web properties by allowing some VariationIDs to not be
transmitted in all contexts. See IsFirstPartyContext() in
variations_http_headers.cc for more details.

Name: kResumeBackgroundVideo
Documentation:
Let videos be resumed via remote controls (for example, the notification)
when in background.

Name: kRetainSuggestionsWithHeaders
Documentation:
If enabled, retains all suggestions with headers to be presented entirely.
Disabling the feature trims the suggestions list to the predefined limit.

Name: kReuseMediaPlayer
Documentation:
Experimental: Try to avoid destroying the media player when transferring a
media element to a new document.  This is a work in progress, and may cause
security and/or stability issues.

Name: kRevokeMediaSourceObjectURLOnAttach
Documentation:
Approach original pre-REC MSE object URL autorevoking behavior, though await
actual attempt to use the object URL for attachment to perform revocation.
This will hopefully reduce runtime memory bloat for pages that do not
explicitly detach their HTMLME+MSE object collections nor explicitly revoke
the object URLs used to attach HTMLME+MSE. When disabled, revocation only
occurs when application explicitly revokes the object URL, or upon the
execution context teardown for the MediaSource object. When enabled,
revocation occurs upon successful start of attachment of HTMLME to the object
URL. Note, rather than immediately scheduling a task to revoke upon the URL's
creation, as at least one other browser does and the original File API
pattern used to follow, this delay until attachment start enables new
scenarios that could use the object URL for attaching HTMLME+MSE cross-thread
(MSE-in-workers), where there could be significant delay between the worker
thread creation of the object URL and the main thread usage of the object URL
for starting attachment to HTMLME.

Name: kRichAutocompletion
Documentation:
If enabled, expands autocompletion to possibly (depending on params) include
suggestion titles and non-prefixes as opposed to be restricted to URL
prefixes. Will also adjust the location bar UI and omnibox text selection to
accommodate the autocompletions.

Name: kRunOnMainThread
Documentation: The feature that gates whether or not the PM runs on the main (UI) thread.

Name: kRunVideoCaptureServiceInBrowserProcess
Documentation:
Run video capture service in the Browser process as opposed to a dedicated
utility process

Name: kSCTAuditing
Documentation: must be always

Name: kSCTAuditingHashdance
