SCT auditing hashdance allows Chrome clients who are not opted-in to Enhanced
Safe Browsing Reporting to perform a k-anonymous query to see if Google knows
about an SCT seen in the wild. If it hasn't been seen, then it is considered
a security incident and uploaded to Google.

Name: kSafeBrowsingCsbrrWithToken
Documentation:
Controls whether Client Safe Browsing Reports are sent with a GAIA-tied token
for Enhanced Safe Browsing users

Name: kSafeBrowsingDisableConsumerCsdForEnterprise
Documentation:
Controls whether we are disabling consumer download checks for users using
the enterprise download checks.

Name: kSafeBrowsingEnterpriseCsd
Documentation:
Controls whether we are performing enterprise download checks for users
with the appropriate policies enabled.

Name: kSafeBrowsingPageLoadToken
Documentation: Controls whether page load tokens are added to Safe Browsing requests.

Name: kSafeBrowsingRemoveCookiesInAuthRequests
Documentation: Controls whether cookies are removed when the access token is present.

Name: kSafeBrowsingSubresourceFilter
Documentation: The primary toggle to enable/disable the Safe Browsing Subresource Filter.

Name: kSamePartyCookiesConsideredFirstParty
Documentation:
When enabled, cookies with the SameParty attribute are treated as
"first-party" when in same-party contexts, for the purposes of third-party
cookie blocking. (Note that as a consequence, some cookies may be blocked
while others are allowed on a cross-site, same-party request. Additionally,
privacy mode is disabled in same-party contexts.)

Name: kSameSiteDefaultChecksMethodRigorously
Documentation:
When enabled, the SameSite by default feature does not add the
"Lax-allow-unsafe" behavior. Any cookies that do not specify a SameSite
attribute will be treated as Lax only, i.e. POST and other unsafe HTTP
methods will not be allowed at all for top-level cross-site navigations.
This only has an effect if the cookie defaults to SameSite=Lax.

Name: kSandboxExternalProtocolBlocked
Documentation:
Gates sandboxed iframe navigation toward external protocol behind any of:
- allow-top-navigation
- allow-top-navigation-to-custom-protocols
- allow-top-navigation-with-user-gesture (+ user gesture)
- allow-popups

Motivation:
Developers are surprised that a sandboxed iframe can navigate and/or
redirect the user toward an external application.
General iframe navigation in sandboxed iframe are not blocked normally,
because they stay within the iframe. However they can be seen as a popup or
a top-level navigation when it leads to opening an external application. In
this case, it makes sense to extend the scope of sandbox flags, to block
malvertising.

Implementation bug: https://crbug.com/1253379
I2S: https://groups.google.com/a/chromium.org/g/blink-dev/c/-t-f7I6VvOI

Enabled in M103. Flag to be removed in M106

Name: kSandboxExternalProtocolBlockedWarning
Documentation: Enabled in M100. Flag to be removed in M106

Name: kSandboxHttpCache
Documentation:
When enabled, certain operations in the HTTP cache are brokered to allow
the network process to be sandboxed.

Name: kSanitizerAPI
Documentation: Controls whether the Sanitizer API is available.

Name: kSanitizerAPINamespaces
Documentation:
Controls whether the Sanitizer API allows namespaced content (SVG + MathML).

This feature is unlikely to be launched as-is. The primary purpose is to
allow testing of different non-standard configurations.

Name: kSaveDataImgSrcset
Documentation:
A feature to enable using the smallest image specified within image srcset
for users with Save Data enabled.

Name: kSavePageAsWebBundle
Documentation: Enables saving pages as Web Bundle.

Name: kScaleTileMemoryLimit
Documentation:
If enabled, the memory limit used for tiles is scaled by
`kScaleTileMemoryLimitFactor`.

Name: kSchedulerSmoothnessForAnimatedScrolls
Documentation:
When enabled, wheel scrolls trigger smoothness mode. When disabled,
smoothness mode is limited to non-animated (precision) scrolls, such as
touch scrolling.

Name: kSchemefulSameSite
Documentation:
When enabled this feature will cause same-site calculations to take into
account the scheme of the site-for-cookies and the request/response url.

Name: kScopeMemoryCachePerContext
Documentation:
Scopes the memory cache to a fetcher i.e. document/frame. Any resource cached
in the blink cache will only be reused if the most recent fetcher that
fetched it was the same as the current document.

Name: kScriptStreaming
Documentation: Controls script streaming.

Name: kScrollUnification
Documentation:
When enabled, all scrolling is performed on the compositor thread -
delegating only the hit test to Blink. This causes Blink to send additional
information in the scroll property tree. When a scroll can't be hit tested
on the compositor, it will post a hit test task to Blink and continue the
scroll when that resolves. For details, see:
https://docs.google.com/document/d/1smLAXs-DSLLmkEt4FIPP7PVglJXOcwRc7A5G0SEwxaY/edit

Name: kSearchResultInlineIcon
Documentation: Enables iconified text and inline icons in launcher search.

Name: kSecondaryServerFieldPredictions
Documentation: Enables considering secondary server field predictions during form parsing.

Name: kSecureContextFixForWorkers
Documentation:
Enables correctly computing whether dedicated workers are secure contexts.
TODO(https://crbug.com/780031): Remove this once fully shipped.

Name: kSecurePaymentConfirmation
Documentation:
Browser-side feature flag for Secure Payment Confirmation (SPC) that also
controls the render side feature state. SPC initial launch is intended
only for Mac devices with Touch ID and and Windows devices with
Windows Hello authentication available and setup.

Name: kSecurePaymentConfirmationDebug
Documentation:
Used to control whether to remove the restriction that PaymentCredential in
WebAuthn and secure payment confirmation method in PaymentRequest API must
use a user verifying platform authenticator. When enabled, this allows using
such devices as UbiKey on Linux, which can make development easier.

Name: kSecurityKeyAttestationPrompt
Documentation: Controls whether the user is prompted when sites request attestation.

Name: kSegmentationModelLowEngagedUsers
Documentation: Feature flag used for running the segmentation model for low engaged users.

Name: kSegmentationPlatformDummyFeature
Documentation:
Feature flag for segmentation platform dummy model that is used for
experimental models and data collection.

Name: kSegmentationPlatformFeature
Documentation: Core feature flag for segmentation platform.

Name: kSegmentationPlatformFeedSegmentFeature
Documentation: Feature flag for enabling Feed user segments feature.

Name: kSegmentationPlatformLowEngagementFeature
Documentation: Feature flag for enabling low engagement segmentation key.

Name: kSegmentationPlatformUkmEngine
Documentation: Feature flag for enabling UKM based engine.

Name: kSegmentationStructuredMetricsFeature
Documentation: Feature flag for allowing structured metrics to be collected.

Name: kSendBeaconThrowForBlobWithNonSimpleType
Documentation: Make sendBeacon throw for a Blob with a non simple type.

Name: kSendCnameAliasesToSubresourceFilterFromBrowser
Documentation:
Enables or disables performing SubresourceFilter checks from the Browser
against any aliases for the requested URL found from DNS CNAME records.

Name: kSendCnameAliasesToSubresourceFilterFromRenderer
Documentation:
Performs additional SubresourceFilter checks when CNAME aliases are found
for the host of a requested URL.

Name: kSendMouseLeaveEvents
Documentation:
This feature allows native ET_MOUSE_EXIT events to be passed
through to blink as mouse leave events. Traditionally these events were
converted to mouse move events due to a number of inconsistencies on
the native platforms. crbug.com/450631

Name: kSendPasswords
Documentation: Enables sending credentials from the settings UI.

Name: kSendSampledPingsForProtegoAllowlistDomains
Documentation:
Controls whether to send sample pings of Protego allowlist domains on
the allowlist to Safe Browsing.

Name: kSendTabToSelfSigninPromo
Documentation:
If this feature is enabled and a signed-out user attempts to share a tab,
they will see a promo to sign-in.

Name: kSendTabToSelfV2
Documentation:
If this feature is enabled, show received tabs in a new UI next to the
profile icon rather than in a system notification.

V2 is the default on desktop and the V1 code path has been deleted there, so
this base::Feature no longer exists on desktop platforms.

Name: kServiceWorkerPaymentApps
Documentation:
Service worker based payment apps as defined by w3c here:
https://w3c.github.io/webpayments-payment-apps-api/
TODO(rouslan): Remove this.

Name: kServiceWorkerTerminationOnNoControllee
Documentation:
Use this feature to experiment terminating a service worker when it doesn't
control any clients: https://crbug.com/1043845.

Name: kServiceWorkerUpdateDelay
Documentation:
Experiment of the delay from navigation to starting an update of a service
worker's script.

Name: kSetLowPriorityForBeacon
Documentation:
When enabled, beacons (and friends) have ResourceLoadPriority::kLow,
not ResourceLoadPriority::kVeryLow.

Name: kSetTimeoutWithoutClamp
Documentation:
If enabled, the setTimeout(..., 0) will not clamp to 1ms.
Tracking bug: https://crbug.com/402694.

Name: kShareCrowButton
Documentation:
Feature that enables the Crow feature.
Owned by the CwF team but located here until it makes sense to create a crow
component, since it is being used in the feed component.

Name: kShareThisTabInsteadButtonGetDisplayMedia
Documentation:
Controls whether a "Share this tab instead" button should be shown for
getDisplayMedia captures. Note: This flag does not control if the "Share this
tab instead" button is shown for chrome.desktopCapture captures.

Name: kShareThisTabInsteadButtonGetDisplayMediaAudio
Documentation:
If kShareThisTabInsteadButtonGetDisplayMedia is ENABLED, this flag controls
whether a "Share this tab instead" button should be enabled for
getDisplayMedia captures with audio.
If kShareThisTabInsteadButtonGetDisplayMedia is DISABLED, this flag has no
effect.
Note: This flag does not control if the "Share this tab instead" button is
shown for chrome.desktopCapture captures.

Name: kSharedArrayBuffer
Documentation:
http://tc39.github.io/ecmascript_sharedmem/shmem.html
This feature is also enabled independently of this flag for cross-origin
isolated renderers.

Name: kSharedArrayBufferOnDesktop
Documentation:
If enabled, SharedArrayBuffer is present and can be transferred on desktop
platforms. This flag is used only as a "kill switch" as we migrate towards
requiring 'crossOriginIsolated'.

Name: kSharedClipboardUI
Documentation: Feature to allow shared clipboard gets processed.

Name: kSharedHighlightingAmp
Documentation: Enables shared highlighting for AMP viewers pages.

Name: kSharedHighlightingRefinedBlocklist
Documentation: Feature flag that enables a narrower blocklist.

Name: kSharedImageManager
Documentation:
Causes us to use the SharedImageManager, removing support for the old
mailbox system. Any consumers of the GPU process using the old mailbox
system will experience undefined results.

Name: kSharedStorageAPI
Documentation:
Enable the shared storage API. This base::Feature directly controls the
corresponding runtime enabled feature.
https://github.com/pythagoraskitty/shared-storage/blob/main/README.md

Name: kSharingMatchPulseInterval
Documentation: Feature flag for matching device expiration to pulse interval.

Name: kSharingMessageBridgeTimeout
Documentation: Feature flag for configuring the timeout in the sharing message bridge.

Name: kSharingPreferVapid
Documentation: Feature flag for prefer sending sharing message using VAPID.

Name: kSharingSendViaSync
Documentation: Feature flag for sending sharing message via Sync.

Name: kShortBookmarkSuggestions
Documentation:
Features used to enable matching short inputs to bookmarks for suggestions.
By default, if both of the following are disabled, input words shorter than 3
  characters won't prefix match bookmarks. E.g., the inputs 'abc x' or 'x'
  won't match bookmark text 'abc xyz'.
If |kShortBookmarkSuggestions()| is enabled, this limitation is lifted and
  both inputs 'abc x' and 'x' can match bookmark text 'abc xyz'.
If |kShortBookmarkSuggestionsByTotalInputLength()| is enabled, matching is
  limited by input length rather than input word length. Input 'abc x' can
  but input 'x' can't match bookmark text 'abc xyz'.

Name: kShortLaxAllowUnsafeThreshold
Documentation:
When enabled, the time threshold for Lax-allow-unsafe cookies will be lowered
from 2 minutes to 10 seconds. This time threshold refers to the age cutoff
for which cookies that default into SameSite=Lax, which are newer than the
threshold, will be sent with any top-level cross-site navigation regardless
of HTTP method (i.e. allowing unsafe methods). This is a convenience for
integration tests which may want to test behavior of cookies older than the
threshold, but which would not be practical to run for 2 minutes.

Name: kShowEnterpriseDialogForAllManagedAccountsSignin
Documentation:
Enables showing the enterprise dialog after every signin into a managed
account.

Name: kSidePanelDragAndDrop
Documentation:
TODO(pbos): Once kReadLater is cleaned up on Desktop, move definition into
ui_features.cc. This is currently temporarily in reading_list_switches.h.

Name: kSignedExchangeReportingForDistributors
Documentation:
Signed Exchange Reporting for distributors
https://www.chromestatus.com/feature/5687904902840320

Name: kSignedExchangeSubresourcePrefetch
Documentation:
Subresource prefetching+loading via Signed HTTP Exchange
https://www.chromestatus.com/feature/5126805474246656

Name: kSignedHTTPExchange
Documentation:
Origin-Signed HTTP Exchanges (for WebPackage Loading)
https://www.chromestatus.com/feature/5745285984681984

Name: kSignedHTTPExchangePingValidity
Documentation: Whether to send a ping to the inner URL upon navigation or not.

Name: kSimplifiedUrlDisplay
Documentation:
Status of the SimplifiedUrlDisplay experiments. This does not control the
individual experiments, those are controlled by their own feature flags.
The feature is only set by Finch so that we can differentiate between
default and control groups of the experiment.

Name: kSiteEngagement
Documentation: Enable site engagement

Name: kSiteIsolationForCrossOriginOpenerPolicy
Documentation:
Controls whether to isolate sites of documents that specify an eligible
Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy header.  Note that this is only intended to be
used on Android, which does not use strict site isolation. See
https://crbug.com/1018656.

Name: kSiteIsolationForGuests
Documentation: This feature turns on site isolation support in <webview> guests.

Name: kSitePerProcess
Documentation:
Alternative to switches::kSitePerProcess, for turning on full site isolation.
Launch bug: https://crbug.com/810843.  This is a //chrome-layer feature to
avoid turning on site-per-process by default for *all* //content embedders
(e.g. this approach lets ChromeCast avoid site-per-process mode).

TODO(alexmos): Move this and the other site isolation features below to
browser_features, as they are only used on the browser side.

Name: kSiteSearchStarterPack
Documentation:
When enabled, adds a "starter pack" of @history, @bookmarks, and @settings
scopes to Site Search/Keyword Mode.

Name: kSkiaDawn
Documentation:
Enable SkiaRenderer Dawn graphics backend. On Windows this will use D3D12,
and on Linux this will use Vulkan.

Name: kSkipCheckForLowEngagedUsers
Documentation: Feature flag to determine whether to skip check for the low engaged users.

Name: kSkipEarlyCommitPendingForCrashedFrame
Documentation:
Enables skipping the early call to CommitPending when navigating away from a
crashed frame.

Name: kSkipInvalidationOptimizationsWhenDeviceInfoUpdated
Documentation:
When enabled, optimization flags (single client and a list of FCM
registration tokens) will be disabled if during the current sync cycle
DeviceInfo has been updated.

Name: kSkipServiceWorkerCheckAll
Documentation: Skip the service worker all install criteria check.

Name: kSkipServiceWorkerCheckInstallOnly
Documentation: Skip the service worker install criteria check for installing WebAPKs.

Name: kSkipTouchEventFilter
Documentation:
Skips the browser touch event filter, ensuring that events that reach the
queue and would otherwise be filtered out will instead be passed onto the
renderer compositor process as long as the page hasn't timed out. If
skip_filtering_process is browser_and_renderer, also skip the renderer cc
touch event filter, ensuring that events will be passed onto the renderer
main thread. Which event types will be always forwarded is controlled by the
"type" FeatureParam, which can be either "discrete" (default) or "all".

Name: kSlidingWindowForDroppedFrameCounter
Documentation:
When enabled, DroppedFrameCounter will use an adjusted sliding window
interval specified by field trial params.

Name: kSmallScriptStreaming
Documentation: Allow streaming small (<30kB) scripts.

Name: kSmartSuggestionForLargeDownloads
Documentation: Whether to enable smart suggestion for large downloads

Name: kSoundContentSetting
Documentation:
Enables or disables the ability to use the sound content setting to mute a
website.

Name: kSpareRendererForSitePerProcess
Documentation:
Controls whether SpareRenderProcessHostManager tries to always have a warm
spare renderer process around for the most recently requested BrowserContext.
This feature is only consulted in site-per-process mode.

Name: kSpeakerChangeDetection
Documentation:
Enable the Speaker Change Detection feature, which inserts a line break when
the Speech On-Device API (SODA) detects a speaker change.

Name: kSpecCompliantCanPlayThrough
Documentation: CanPlayThrough issued according to standard.

Name: kSpeculationRulesPrefetchProxy
Documentation:
Enable the use of Speculation Rules in access the private prefetch proxy
(chrome/browser/prefetch/prefetch_proxy/).
https://crbug.com/1190167

Name: kSplitAuthCacheByNetworkIsolationKey
Documentation:
Enables or defaults splittup up server (not proxy) entries in the
HttpAuthCache.

Name: kSplitCacheByIncludeCredentials
Documentation: Splits cache entries by the request's includeCredentials.

Name: kSplitCacheByNetworkIsolationKey
Documentation:
Splits cache entries by the request's NetworkIsolationKey if one is
available.
AboutFlagOs: kOsWin | kOsLinux | kOsLacros | kOsMac | kOsCrOS | kOsAndroid | kOsFuchsia

Name: kSplitClusteringTasksToSmallerBatches
Documentation: Splits clustering task into smaller batches.

Name: kSplitDnsByNetworkIsolationKey
Documentation: Splits dns requests by the request's NetworkIsolationKey.
AboutFlagOs: kOsWin | kOsLinux | kOsMac | kOsCrOS | kOsAndroid | kOsFuchsia

Name: kSplitHostCacheByNetworkIsolationKey
Documentation:
Splits host cache entries by the DNS request's NetworkIsolationKey if one is
available. Also prevents merging live DNS lookups when there is a NIK
mismatch.

Name: kStaticKeyPinningEnforcement
Documentation: Controls whether static key pinning is enforced.

Name: kStopInBackground
Documentation:
Freeze scheduler task queues in background after allowed grace time.
"stop" is a legacy name.

Name: kStorageAccessAPI
Documentation: Enable the Storage Access API. https://crbug.com/989663.

Name: kStrictOriginIsolation
Documentation:
Controls whether site isolation should use origins instead of scheme and
eTLD+1.

Name: kSubframeShutdownDelay
Documentation:
Delays RenderProcessHost shutdown by a few seconds to allow the subframe's
process to be potentially reused. This aims to reduce process churn in
navigations where the source and destination share subframes.

Name: kSubresourceWebBundles
Documentation: Enables subresource loading with Web Bundles.

Name: kSubstringSetTreeForAttributeBuckets
Documentation:
If enabled, CSS rulesets with many different rules on the same attribute
will be attempted accelerated with a substring set tree.

Name: kSupportSearchSuggestionForPrerender2
Documentation:
This flag controls whether to trigger prerendering when the default search
engine suggests to prerender a search result. It also enables
Prerender2-related features on the blink side. This flag takes effect only
when blink::features::Prerender2 is enabled.

Name: kSupportTool
Documentation:
Enables the demo version of the Support Tool. The tool will be available in
chrome://support-tool. See go/support-tool-v1-design for more details.

Name: kSuppressDifferentOriginSubframeJSDialogs
Documentation:
Disallows window.{alert, prompt, confirm} if triggered inside a subframe that
is not same origin with the main frame.

Name: kSurfaceSyncThrottling
Documentation:
Used by CC to throttle frame production of older surfaces. Used by the
Browser to batch SurfaceSync calls sent to the Renderer for properties can
change in close proximity to each other.

Name: kSuspendMutedAudio
Documentation:
Disables the real audio output stream after silent audio has been delivered
for too long. Should save quite a bit of power in the muted video case.

Name: kSuspiciousSiteTriggerQuotaFeature
Documentation: Controls the daily quota for the suspicious site trigger.

Name: kSwipeToMoveCursor
Documentation: Android only feature, for swipe to move cursor.

Name: kSyncAllowWalletDataInTransportModeWithCustomPassphrase
Documentation:
Allows custom passphrase users to receive Wallet data for secondary accounts
while in transport-only mode.

Name: kSyncExtensionTypesThrottling
Documentation:
Causes the sync engine to count a quota for commits of data types that can
be committed by extension JS API. If the quota is depleted, an extra long
nudge delay is applied to that data type. As a result, more changes are
likely to get combined into one commit message.

Name: kSyncFilterOutInactiveDevicesForSingleClient
Documentation:
Enables filtering out inactive devices which haven't sent DeviceInfo update
recently (depending on the device's pulse_interval and an additional margin).

Name: kSyncPromoAfterSigninIntercept
Documentation: Enables the sync promo after the sign-in intercept.

Name: kSyncRequiresPoliciesLoaded
Documentation: Sync requires policies to be loaded before starting.

Name: kSyncReuploadBookmarks
Documentation:
TODO(crbug.com/1232951): remove the feature toggle once most of bookmarks
have been reuploaded.

Name: kSyncSendInterestedDataTypes
Documentation:
If enabled, interested data types, excluding Wallet and Offer, will be sent
to the Sync Server as part of DeviceInfo.

Name: kSyncTrustedVaultPassphrasePromo
Documentation:
Whether the entry point to opt in to trusted vault in settings should be
shown.

Name: kSyncTrustedVaultPassphraseRecovery
Documentation:
Keep this entry in sync with the equivalent name in
ChromeFeatureList.java.

Name: kSyncUseFCMRegistrationTokensList
Documentation:
Sync invalidation switches.

Enables providing the list of FCM registration tokens in the commit request.

Name: kSynchronizedScrolling
Documentation:
Whether the compositor should attempt to sync with the scroll handlers before
submitting a frame.

Name: kSynchronousPageFlipTesting
Documentation:
Indicates whether DrmOverlayManager should used the synchronous API to
perform pageflip tests.

Name: kSyntheticPointerActions
Documentation:
Dispatch touch events to "SyntheticGestureController" for events from
Devtool Protocol Input.dispatchTouchEvent to simulate touch events close to
real OS events.

Name: kSystemCaptionStyle
Documentation: Allows system caption style for WebVTT Captions.

Name: kSystemCursorSizeSupported
Documentation:
When enabled, the feature will query the OS for a default cursor size,
to be used in determining the concrete object size of a custom cursor in
blink.

Name: kSystemKeyboardLock
Documentation: Allows system keyboard event capture via the keyboard lock API.

Name: kTFLiteLanguageDetectionEnabled
Documentation: Controls whether the TFLite-based language detection is enabled.

Name: kTLS13KeyUpdate
Documentation:
Enables sending TLS 1.3 Key Update messages on TLS 1.3 connections in order
to ensure that this corner of the spec is exercised. This is currently
disabled by default because we discovered incompatibilities with some
servers.

Name: kTabRanker
Documentation:
Enables using the Tab Ranker to score tabs for discarding instead of relying
on last focused time.

Name: kTabSwitchMetrics2
Documentation:
If enabled, ContentToVisibleTimeReporter logs
Browser.Tabs.TotalSwitchDuration2.* instead of
Browser.Tabs.TotalSwitchDuration.*.

Name: kTailoredSecurityIntegration
Documentation: Controls whether the integration of tailored security settings is enabled.

Name: kTaskPerMessage
Documentation:
Enables a task to be scheduled for each individual message dispatched to a
Mojo binding endpoint (or reply to an InterfacePtr).

When disabled, dispatch happens eagerly in batch, so when a binding is
scheduled to dispatch messages, it fully flushes and dispatches all queued
messages within the extent of a single scheduler task.

Enabling this feature allows for more fine-grained performance control
through the scheduler, but may initially cause some important edge cases to
regress in performance due to high-priority messages seeing increased
latency. Ideally we'd address these cases by giving the affected bindings
higher-priority TaskRunners.

Name: kTextFragmentAnchor
Documentation: Enable text snippets in URL fragments. https://crbug.com/919204.

Name: kThirdPartyStoragePartitioning
Documentation:
Enables partitioning of third party storage (IndexedDB, CacheStorage, etc.)
by the top level site to reduce fingerprinting.

Name: kThreadWrapperUsesMetronome
Documentation:
Whether ThreadWrapper should schedule low-precision tasks on the metronome.
Default: disabled.

Name: kThreadingOptimizationsOnIO
Documentation:
Whether optimizations controlled by kNavigationThreadingOptimizations are
moved to the IO thread or a separate background thread.

Name: kThreatDomDetailsTagAndAttributeFeature
Documentation:
Specifies which non-resource HTML Elements to collect based on their tag and
attributes. It's a single param containing a comma-separated list of pairs.
For example: "tag1,id,tag1,height,tag2,foo" - this will collect elements with
tag "tag1" that have attribute "id" or "height" set, and elements of tag
"tag2" if they have attribute "foo" set. All tag names and attributes should
be lower case.

Name: kThrottleDelayable
Documentation:
Based on the field trial parameters, this feature will override the value of
the maximum number of delayable requests allowed in flight. The number of
delayable requests allowed in flight will be based on the network's
effective connection type ranges and the
corresponding number of delayable requests in flight specified in the
experiment configuration. Based on field trial parameters, this experiment
may also throttle delayable requests based on the number of non-delayable
requests in-flight times a weighting factor.

Name: kThrottleDisplayNoneAndVisibilityHiddenCrossOriginIframes
Documentation:
Forces same-process display:none cross-origin iframes to be throttled in the
same manner that OOPIFs are.

Name: kThrottleForegroundTimers
Documentation: Throttles Javascript timer wake ups on foreground pages.

Name: kThrottleInstallingServiceWorker
Documentation:
Enable throttling of fetch() requests from service workers in the
installing state.  The limit of 3 was chosen to match the limit
in background main frames.  In addition, trials showed that this
did not cause excessive timeouts and resulted in a net improvement
in successful install rate on some platforms.

Name: kTimeoutTcpConnectAttempt
Documentation:
Enables a timeout on individual TCP connect attempts, based on
the parameter values.

Name: kToolbarUseHardwareBitmapDraw
Documentation:
Determines how screenshots of the toolbar uses Software or Hardware drawing.
Works on Android 10+.

Name: kTouchDragAndContextMenu
Documentation:
This feature allows touch dragging and a context menu to occur
simultaneously, with the assumption that the menu is non-modal.  Without this
feature, a long-press touch gesture can start either a drag or a context-menu
in Blink, not both (more precisely, a context menu is shown only if a drag
cannot be started).

Name: kTouchToFillPasswordSubmission
Documentation:
Enables the experiment to automatically submit a form after filling by
TouchToFill

Name: kTouchpadAsyncPinchEvents
Documentation:
Enables async touchpad pinch zoom events. We check the ACK of the first
synthetic wheel event in a pinch sequence, then send the rest of the
synthetic wheel events of the pinch sequence as non-blocking if the first
event’s ACK is not canceled.

Name: kTouchpadOverscrollHistoryNavigation
Documentation:
Allows swipe left/right from touchpad change browser navigation. Currently
only enabled by default on CrOS, LaCrOS and Windows.

Name: kTracingServiceInProcess
Documentation:
The features should be documented alongside the definition of their values
in the .cc file.

Name: kTrackCurrentShaders
Documentation:
Track current program's shaders at glUseProgram() call for crash report
purpose. Only effective on Windows because the attached shaders may only
be reliably retrieved with ANGLE backend.

Name: kTranslate
Documentation:
This allows the user to disable translate by using the
`--disable-features=Translate` command-line flag.

Name: kTranslateAssistContent
Documentation: This feature enables providing Translate data to Assistant.

Name: kTranslateAutoSnackbars
Documentation:
Feature flag used to control the auto-always and auto-never snackbar
parameters (i.e. threshold and maximum-number-of).

Name: kTranslateCompactUI
Documentation: Feature flag for "Translate Compact Infobar UI" project.

Name: kTranslateIntent
Documentation: This feature enables an intent that starts translating the foreground tab.

Name: kTranslateRankerQuery
Documentation:
Features used to enable ranker query, enforcement and logging. Note that
enabling enforcement implies (forces) enabling queries.

Name: kTranslateRecentTarget
Documentation:
Enables or disables using the most recent target language as the default
target language option.

Name: kTranslateSubFrames
Documentation:
Controls whether translation applies to sub frames as well as the
main frame.

Name: kTreatBootstrapAsDefault
Documentation:
When TreatBootstrapAsDefault is enabled, the browser will execute tasks with
the kBootstrap task type on the default task queues (based on priority of
the task) rather than a dedicated high-priority task queue. Intended to
evaluate the impact of the already-launched prioritization of bootstrap
tasks (crbug.com/1258621).

Name: kTreatUnsafeDownloadsAsActive
Documentation:
Disable downloads of unsafe file types over insecure transports if initiated
from a secure page. As of M89, mixed downloads are blocked on all platforms.

Name: kTriggerNetworkDataMigration
Documentation:
Enables migration of the network context data from `unsandboxed_data_path` to
`data_path`. See the explanation in network_context.mojom.

Name: kTriggerThrottlerDailyQuotaFeature
Documentation:
Controls the daily quota for data collection triggers. It's a single param
containing a comma-separated list of pairs. The format of the param is
"T1,Q1,T2,Q2,...Tn,Qn", where Tx is a TriggerType and Qx is how many reports
that trigger is allowed to send per day.
TODO(crbug.com/744869): This param should be deprecated after ad sampler
launch in favour of having a unique quota feature and param per trigger.
Having a single shared feature makes it impossible to run multiple trigger
trials simultaneously.

Name: kTrimWebCacheOnMemoryPressureOnly
Documentation:
Disable the logic that try to coordinate the in-memory cache resource usage
of all renderers and simply trim the caches on memory pressure. Renderers
get a memory pressure signal a few minutes after they've been backgrounded.

Name: kTrustTokens
Documentation:
Enables preprocessing requests with the Trust Tokens API Fetch flags set,
and handling their responses, according to the protocol.
(See https://github.com/WICG/trust-token-api.)

Name: kTrustedDOMTypes
Documentation: Controls whether the Trusted Types API is available.

Name: kTurnOffStreamingMediaCachingAlways
Documentation: Turns off streaming media caching to disk always.

Name: kTurnOffStreamingMediaCachingOnBattery
Documentation: Turns off streaming media caching to disk when on battery power.

Name: kUACHOverrideBlank
Documentation:
Changes behavior of User-Agent Client Hints to send blank headers when the
User-Agent string is overridden, instead of disabling the headers altogether.

Name: kUACHPlatformEnabledByDefault
Documentation: Enable "Sec-CH-UA-Platform" client hint and request header for all requests

Name: kUIDebugTools
Documentation: Enables UI debugging tools such as shortcuts.

Name: kUIDebugToolsEnableSyntheticEvents
Documentation:
Enables UI debugging tools to send synthetic events.
This is used by the telemetry benchmarking tools only.

Name: kUIExperimentMaxAutocompleteMatches
Documentation:
Feature used to cap max suggestions shown according to the params
UIMaxAutocompleteMatches and UIMaxAutocompleteMatchesByProvider.

Name: kURLLoaderSyncClient
Documentation:
Whether the sync client optimization is used for communication between the
CorsURLLoader and URLLoader.

Name: kUdpSocketPosixAlwaysUpdateBytesReceived
Documentation:
When enabled, UDPSocketPosix increments the global counter of bytes received
every time bytes are received, instead of using a timer to batch updates.
This should reduce the number of wake ups and improve battery consumption.
TODO(https://crbug.com/1189805): Cleanup the feature after verifying that it
doesn't negatively affect performance.

Name: kUiCompositorScrollWithLayers
Documentation: Enables scrolling with layers under ui using the ui::Compositor.

Name: kUkmFeature
Documentation: This feature controls whether UkmService should be created.

Name: kUmaBackgroundSessions
Documentation: If enabled, keep logging and reporting UMA while chrome is backgrounded.

Name: kUnifiedAutoplay
Documentation:
Enables the Unified Autoplay policy by overriding the platform's default
autoplay policy.

Name: kUnifiedCredentialManagerDryRun
Documentation:
Enables the intent fetching for the credential manager in Google Mobile
Services. It does not enable launching the credential manager.

Name: kUnifiedPasswordManagerAndroid
Documentation:
Enables use of Google Mobile Services for password storage. Chrome's local
database will be unused but kept in sync for local passwords.

Name: kUnifiedPasswordManagerSyncUsingAndroidBackendOnly
Documentation:
If enabled, the built-in sync functionality in PasswordSyncBridge becomes
unused, meaning that SyncService/SyncEngine will no longer download or
upload changes to/from the Sync server. Instead, an external Android-specific
backend will be used to achieve similar behavior.

Name: kUnrestrictedSharedArrayBuffer
Documentation:
This feature is for a reverse Origin Trial, enabling SharedArrayBuffer for
sites as they migrate towards requiring cross-origin isolation for these
features.
TODO(bbudge): Remove when the deprecation is complete.
https://developer.chrome.com/origintrials/#/view_trial/303992974847508481
https://crbug.com/1144104

Name: kUpdateHistoryEntryPointsInIncognito
Documentation: When enabled, removes any entry points to the history UI from Incognito mode.

Name: kUpdatedConnectionSecurityIndicators
Documentation: Experiment to introduce new security indicators for HTTPS.

Name: kUseAXPositionForDocumentMarkers
Documentation:
Once this flag is enabled, a single codebase in AXPosition will be used for
handling document markers on all platforms, including the announcement of
spelling mistakes.

Name: kUseAndroidOverlayForSecureOnly
Documentation:
Use AndroidOverlay only if required for secure video playback. This requires
that |kOverlayFullscreenVideo| is true, else it is ignored.

Name: kUseAudioLatencyFromHAL
Documentation:
Use the (hacky) AudioManager.getOutputLatency() call to get the estimated
hardware latency for a stream for OpenSLES playback.  This is normally not
needed, except for some Android TV devices.

Name: kUseButtonTranslateBubbleUi
Documentation: This feature uses the existing UI for translate bubble.

Name: kUseChimeAndroidSdk
Documentation: The feature flag to determine whether to use Chime Android SDK.

Name: kUseClientConfigIPH
Documentation:
A feature for enabling In-Product Help (IPH) to use client side
configuration. When this flag is enabled, finch config will be ignored for
all IPHs.

Name: kUseCommonSelectPopup
Documentation: Used to enable the common select popup.

Name: kUseDecoderStreamForWebRTC
Documentation:
If enabled, RTCVideoDecoderAdapter will wrap a DecoderStream as a video
decoder, rather than using MojoVideoDecoder.  This causes the RTC external
decoder to have all the decoder selection / fallback/forward logic of the
non-RTC pipeline.
TODO(liberato): This also causes the external decoder to use software
decoding sometimes, which changes the interpretation of "ExternalDecoder".

Name: kUseDnsHttpsSvcb
Documentation:
Enables querying HTTPS DNS records that will affect results from HostResolver
and may be used to affect connection behavior. Whether or not those results
are used (e.g. to connect via ECH) may be controlled by separate features.

Not to be confused with `kDnsHttpssvc` which is for experiment-only queries
where received HTTPS results do not affect Chrome behavior and are only used
for metrics.

Name: kUseDownloadOfflineContentProvider
Documentation: Whether offline content provider should be used for the downloads UI..

Name: kUseEngagementScoreCache
Documentation: Uses an in-memory cache that stores engagement score.

Name: kUseFeatureEngagementForUserTargeting
Documentation:
Feature flag to determine whether feature engagement tracker should be used
instead of segmentation platform.

Name: kUseFiveMinutesThreadReclaimTime
Documentation:
Whether threads in the ThreadPool should be reclaimed after being idle for 5
minutes, instead of 30 seconds.

Name: kUseGles2ForOopR
Documentation: Used to limit GL version to 2.0 for skia raster on Android.

Name: kUseInProgressDownloadManagerForDownloadService
Documentation:
Whether in-progress download manager will be used to initialize download
service.

Name: kUseManagementService
Documentation:
Enables using policy::ManagementService to get the browser's and platform
management state everywhere.

Name: kUseMediaHistoryStore
Documentation: Enables using the media history store to store media engagement metrics.

Name: kUseNewDownloadWarnings
Documentation: Controls whether Chrome uses new download warning UX.

Name: kUsePageViewportInLCP
Documentation:
Uses page viewport instead of frame viewport in the Largest Contentful Paint
heuristic where images occupying the full viewport are ignored.

Name: kUseParallelRequestsForHTTP2
Documentation: Whether parallel download is used for HTTP2 connections.

Name: kUseParallelRequestsForQUIC
Documentation: Whether parallel download is used for QUIC connections.

Name: kUsePlatformDelegatedInk
Documentation:
Enables platform supported delegated ink trails instead of Skia backed
delegated ink trails.

Name: kUsePooledSharedImageVideoProvider
Documentation:
Enable pooling of SharedImageVideo objects for use by MCVD, to save a hop to
the GPU main thread during VideoFrame construction.

Name: kUsePopularSitesSuggestions
Documentation: If this feature is enabled, we enable popular sites in the suggestions UI.

Name: kUseR16Texture
Documentation: Use R16 texture for 9-16 bit channel instead of half-float conversion by CPU.

Name: kUseRealBuffersForPageFlipTest
Documentation:
Whether we should use the real buffers corresponding to overlay candidates in
order to do a pageflip test rather than allocating test buffers.

Name: kUseRealColorSpaceForAndroidVideo
Documentation:
Historically we hardcoded sRGB for color space. This flags controls if we
pass real color space to VideoFrame/SharedImages.

Name: kUseResourceFetchPriority
Documentation:
Enables using a resource's fetch priority to determine the priority of the
resource's loading tasks posted to blink's scheduler.

Name: kUseResourceFetchPriorityOnlyWhenLoading
Documentation:
Enables using a resource's fetch priority to determine the priority of the
resource's loading tasks posted to blink's scheduler only for resources
requested during the loading phase.

Name: kUseSkiaRenderer
Documentation: Use the SkiaRenderer.

Name: kUseSnappyForParkableStrings
Documentation:
Enabling this will cause parkable strings to use Snappy for compression iff
kCompressParkableStrings is enabled.

Name: kUseSurfaceLayerForVideoDefault
Documentation:
Hardcoded as disabled for WebView to have a different default for
UseSurfaceLayerForVideo from chrome.

Name: kUseSyncInvalidations
Documentation:
If enabled, the device will register with FCM and listen to new
invalidations. Also, FCM token will be set in DeviceInfo, which signals to
the server that device listens to new invalidations.
The device will not subscribe to old invalidations for any data types except
Wallet and Offer, since that will be covered by the new system.
SyncSendInterestedDataTypes must be enabled for this to take effect.

Name: kUseSyncInvalidationsForWalletAndOffer
Documentation:
If enabled, types related to Wallet and Offer will be included in interested
data types, and the device will listen to new invalidations for those types
(if they are enabled).
The device will not register for old invalidations at all.
UseSyncInvalidations must be enabled for this to take effect.

Name: kUserActivationSameOriginVisibility
Documentation:
Allows user activation propagation to all frames having the same origin as
the activation notifier frame.  This is an intermediate measure before we
have an iframe attribute to declaratively allow user activation propagation
to subframes.

Name: kUserAgentClientHint
Documentation:
An experimental replacement for the `User-Agent` header, defined in
https://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-west-ua-client-hints.

Name: kUserAgentClientHintFullVersionList
Documentation: Enable `sec-ch-ua-full-version-list` client hint.

Name: kUserAgentOverrideExperiment
Documentation:
Experiment for measuring how often an overridden User-Agent string is made by
appending or prepending to the original User-Agent string.

Name: kUserLevelMemoryPressureSignal
Documentation: Enables user level memory pressure signal generation on Android.

Name: kUserMediaCaptureOnFocus
Documentation:
If enabled, GetUserMedia API will only work when the concerned tab is in
focus

Name: kUserMediaScreenCapturing
Documentation: Screen Capture API support for Android

Name: kUserNotes
Documentation: Feature controlling the User Notes feature on desktop platforms.

Name: kUserVisibleDebug
Documentation:
Enables debug info in user-visible surfaces, like the actual WebUI page.
Does nothing if `kJourneys` is disabled.

Name: kUsernameFirstFlow
Documentation:
Enables support of sending votes on username first flow. The votes are sent
on single username forms and are based on user interaction with the save
prompt.
TODO(crbug.com/959776): Clean up code 2-3 milestones after the launch.

Name: kUsernameFirstFlowFallbackCrowdsourcing
Documentation:
Enables support of sending additional votes on username first flow. The votes
are sent on single password forms and contain information about preceding
single username forms.

Name: kUsernameFirstFlowFilling
Documentation:
Enables support of filling and saving on username first flow.
TODO(crbug.com/959776): Clean up code 2-3 milestones after the launch.

Name: kV8CodeMemoryWriteProtection
Documentation:
Enables W^X code memory protection in V8.
This is enabled in V8 by default. To test the performance impact, we are
going to disable this feature in a finch experiment.

Name: kV8CompactCodeSpaceWithStack
Documentation: Enable code space compaction when finalizing a full GC with stack.

Name: kV8CompactMaps
Documentation: Enables compaction of maps in a full GC.

Name: kV8CompactWithStack
Documentation: Enable compaction when finalizing a full GC with stack.

Name: kV8ConcurrentSparkplug
Documentation: Enables the concurrent Sparkplug compiler.

Name: kV8CrashOnEvacuationFailure
Documentation: Crashes on evacuation failures in a full GC instead of aborting evacuation.

Name: kV8ExperimentalRegexpEngine
Documentation: Enables fallback to a breadth-first regexp engine on excessive backtracking.

Name: kV8FlushBaselineCode
Documentation: Enables flushing of baseline code in V8.

Name: kV8FlushBytecode
Documentation: Enables flushing of JS bytecode in V8.

Name: kV8FlushEmbeddedBlobICache
Documentation: Enables flushing of the instruction cache for the embedded blob.

Name: kV8LazyFeedbackAllocation
Documentation: Enables lazy feedback allocation in V8.

Name: kV8NoReclaimUnmodifiedWrappers
Documentation: Disables reclaiming of unmodified wrappers objects.

Name: kV8OffThreadFinalization
Documentation: Enables finalizing streaming JS compilations on a background thread.

Name: kV8OptimizeJavascript
Documentation: Enables optimization of JavaScript in V8.

Name: kV8OptimizeWorkersForPerformance
Documentation:
Prevents workers from sending IsolateInBackgroundNotification to V8
and thus instructs V8 to favor performance over memory on workers.

Name: kV8PerContextMarkingWorklist
Documentation: Enables per-context marking worklists in V8 GC.

Name: kV8PerFrameMemoryMonitoring
Documentation: Enables or disables per-frame memory monitoring.

Name: kV8ReduceConcurrentMarkingTasks
Documentation: Enables reduced number of concurrent marking tasks.

Name: kV8ScriptAblation
Documentation: Artificially delays script execution.

Name: kV8ShortBuiltinCalls
Documentation: Enables short builtin calls feature.

Name: kV8SlowHistograms
Documentation:
Enables slow histograms that provide detailed information at increased
runtime overheads.

Name: kV8SlowHistogramsCodeMemoryWriteProtection
Documentation:
Multiple finch experiments might use slow-histograms. We introduce
separate feature flags to circumvent finch limitations.

Name: kV8Sparkplug
Documentation:
Enables Sparkplug compiler. Note that this only sets the V8 flag when
manually overridden; otherwise it defers to whatever the V8 default is.

Name: kV8SparkplugNeedsShortBuiltinCalls
Documentation:
Makes sure the experimental Sparkplug compiler is only enabled if short
builtin calls are enabled too.

Name: kV8TurboFastApiCalls
Documentation: Enables fast API calls in TurboFan.

Name: kV8Turboprop
Documentation: Enables experimental Turboprop compiler.

Name: kV8UseMapSpace
Documentation: Enables a separate heap space for all map objects.

Name: kV8VirtualMemoryCage
Documentation:
Enables the experimental V8 sandbox. This is called V8VirtualMemoryCage
instead of V8Sandbox for historical reasons.
TODO(1218005) remove this once the finch trial has ended.

Name: kV8VmFuture
Documentation: Enables future V8 VM features

Name: kVaapiAV1Decoder
Documentation: Enable VA-API hardware decode acceleration for AV1.

Name: kVaapiEnforceVideoMinMaxResolution
Documentation:
Reject creation of encode/decode VAContexts when the requested resolution is
outside the enumerated minimum and maximum. TODO(b/171041334): Remove and
enable by default once the ARC++ hw codecs issue is fixed.

Name: kVaapiJpegImageDecodeAcceleration
Documentation:
Controls the decode acceleration of JPEG images (as opposed to camera
captures) in Chrome OS using the VA-API.
TODO(andrescj): remove or enable by default in Chrome OS once
https://crbug.com/868400 is resolved.

Name: kVaapiLowPowerEncoderGen9x
Documentation: Enable VA-API hardware low power encoder for all codecs on intel Gen9x gpu.

Name: kVaapiVP8Encoder
Documentation: Enable VA-API hardware encode acceleration for VP8.

Name: kVaapiVP9Encoder
Documentation: Enable VA-API hardware encode acceleration for VP9.

Name: kVaapiVideoMinResolutionForPerformance
Documentation:
Ensure the advertised minimum supported resolution is larger than or equal to
a given one (likely QVGA + 1) for certain codecs/modes and platforms, for
performance reasons. This does not affect JPEG decoding.

Name: kVaapiWebPImageDecodeAcceleration
Documentation:
Controls the decode acceleration of WebP images in Chrome OS using the
VA-API.
TODO(gildekel): remove or enable by default in Chrome OS once
https://crbug.com/877694 is resolved.

Name: kVerifyDidCommitParams
Documentation:
Enables comparing browser and renderer's DidCommitProvisionalLoadParams in
RenderFrameHostImpl::VerifyThatBrowserAndRendererCalculatedDidCommitParamsMatch.

Name: kVerticalSnap
Documentation: Enable Vertical Snap.

Name: kVibration
Documentation: Enables vibration; an user gesture will still be required if enabled.

Name: kVideoBlitColorAccuracy
Documentation: Inform video blitter of video color space.

Name: kVideoPlaybackQuality
Documentation: Controls whether the <video>.getVideoPlaybackQuality() API is enabled.

Name: kVideoTutorials
Documentation: Main feature flag for the video tutorials feature.

Name: kViewportHeightClientHintHeader
Documentation:
Controls whether the Viewport Height client hint can be added to request
headers.

Name: kVisualFeaturesInCsppPings
Documentation: Controls whether we send visual features in CSPP pings.

Name: kVisualFeaturesSizes
Documentation:
Controls the behavior of visual features in CSD pings. This feature is
checked for the final size of the visual features and the minimum size of
the screen.

Name: kVizFrameSubmissionForWebView
Documentation:
Submit CompositorFrame from SynchronousLayerTreeFrameSink directly to viz in
WebView.

Name: kVp9kSVCHWDecoding
Documentation: Enable VP9 k-SVC decoding with HW decoder for webrtc use case.

Name: kVulkan
Documentation:
Enable Vulkan graphics backend for compositing and rasterization. Defaults to
native implementation if --use-vulkan flag is not used. Otherwise
--use-vulkan will be followed.
Note Android WebView uses kWebViewVulkan instead of this.

Name: kVulkanFromANGLE
Documentation: Enable sharing Vulkan device queue with ANGLE's Vulkan backend.

Name: kWakeUpAfterGetWork
Documentation:
Under this feature, another WorkerThread is signaled only after the current
thread was assigned work.

Name: kWakeUpStrategyFeature
Documentation: Under this feature, a given WakeUpStrategy param is used.

Name: kWarmUpNetworkProcess
Documentation: Pre-warm up the network process on browser startup.

Name: kWebApkInstallService
Documentation: Enables the Chrome Android WebAPK-install service.

Name: kWebAppEnableDarkMode
Documentation:
Enables web apps to provide theme color and background color overrides for
dark mode.

Name: kWebAppEnableHandleLinks
Documentation:
Enables the "handle_links" manifest field for web apps.
Explainer:
https://github.com/WICG/pwa-url-handler/blob/main/handle_links/explainer.md

Name: kWebAppEnableLaunchHandler
Documentation:
Enables the "launch_handler" manifest field for web apps.
Explainer: https://github.com/WICG/sw-launch/blob/main/launch_handler.md

Name: kWebAppEnableLaunchHandlerV1API
kWebAppEnableManifestId
Documentation:
Enables Unique ID feature in web apps. Controls parsing of "id" field in web
app manifests. See explainer for more information:
https://github.com/philloooo/pwa-unique-id

Name: kWebAppEnableTranslations
Documentation: Enables the "translations" manifest field for web apps.

Name: kWebAppEnableUrlHandlers
Documentation:
Controls URL handling feature in web apps. Controls parsing of "url_handlers"
field in web app manifests. See explainer for more information:
https://github.com/WICG/pwa-url-handler/blob/main/explainer.md

Name: kWebAppManifestLockScreen
Documentation:
Controls parsing of the "lock_screen" dictionary field and its "start_url"
entry in web app manifests.  See explainer for more information:
https://github.com/WICG/lock-screen/
Note: the lock screen API and OS integration is separately controlled by
the content feature `kWebLockScreenApi`.

Name: kWebAppWindowControlsOverlay
Documentation: Enable window controls overlays for desktop PWAs
AboutFlagOs: kOsWin | kOsLinux | kOsLacros | kOsMac | kOsCrOS | kOsFuchsia

Name: kWebAssemblyBaseline
Documentation: Enable WebAssembly baseline compilation (Liftoff).

Name: kWebAssemblyCodeProtection
Documentation: Enable memory protection for code JITed for WebAssembly.

Name: kWebAssemblyDynamicTiering
Documentation: Enable WebAssembly dynamic tiering (only tier up hot functions).

Name: kWebAssemblyLazyCompilation
Documentation: Enable WebAssembly lazy compilation (JIT on first call).

Name: kWebAssemblySimd
Documentation:
Enable WebAssembly SIMD.
https://github.com/WebAssembly/Simd

Name: kWebAssemblyTiering
Documentation: Enable WebAssembly tiering (Liftoff -> TurboFan).

Name: kWebAssemblyTrapHandler
Documentation: Enable WebAssembly trap handler.

Name: kWebAuthCable
Documentation: disabled in Bromite

Name: kWebAuthCableDisco
Documentation: Enable discoverable credentials on caBLE authenticators.

Name: kWebAuthCableExtensionAnywhere
Documentation: Support the caBLE extension in assertion requests from any origin.

Name: kWebAuthConditionalUI
Documentation: Controls whether WebAuthn conditional UI requests are supported.

Name: kWebAuthnGoogleCorpRemoteDesktopClientPrivilege
Documentation:
Feature flag for the Google-internal
`WebAuthenticationAllowGoogleCorpRemoteRequestProxying` enterprise policy.

Name: kWebBluetooth
Documentation:
Controls whether the Web Bluetooth API is enabled:
https://webbluetoothcg.github.io/web-bluetooth/

Name: kWebBluetoothBondOnDemand
Documentation:
Controls whether Web Bluetooth will automatically start the bonding process,
to allow access to characteristics requiring a secure connection.

Name: kWebBluetoothNewPermissionsBackend
Documentation:
Controls whether Web Bluetooth should use the new permissions backend. The
new permissions backend uses ChooserContextBase, which is used by other
device APIs, such as WebUSB. When enabled, WebBluetoothWatchAdvertisements
and WebBluetoothGetDevices blink features are also enabled.

Name: kWebBundles
Documentation:
Controls whether Web Bundles (Bundled HTTP Exchanges) is enabled.
https://wicg.github.io/webpackage/draft-yasskin-wpack-bundled-exchanges.html
When this feature is enabled, Chromium can load unsigned Web Bundles local
file under file:// URL (and content:// URI on Android).

Name: kWebBundlesFromNetwork
Documentation:
When this feature is enabled, Chromium will be able to load unsigned Web
Bundles file under https: URL and localhost http: URL.
TODO(crbug.com/1018640): Implement this feature.

Name: kWebFeed
Documentation: Feature that allows users to keep up with and consume web content.

Name: kWebFeedAwareness
Documentation: Feature that provides the user assistance in discovering the web feed.

Name: kWebFeedOnboarding
Documentation: Feature that provides the user assistance in using the web feed.

Name: kWebFeedSort
Documentation: Feature that enables sorting by different heuristics in the web feed.

Name: kWebFontsCacheAwareTimeoutAdaption
Documentation:
Enables cache-aware WebFonts loading. See https://crbug.com/570205.
The feature is disabled on Android for WebView API issue discussed at
https://crbug.com/942440.

Name: kWebGLImageChromium
Documentation:
If WebGL Image Chromium is allowed, this feature controls whether it is
enabled.

Name: kWebGPUService
Documentation:
Enable WebGPU on gpu service side only. This is used with origin trial
before gpu service is enabled by default.

Name: kWebMeasureMemoryViaPerformanceManager
Documentation:
Controls whether the implementation of the performance.measureMemory
web API uses PerformanceManager or not.

Name: kWebMidi
Documentation:
Enable the browser process components of the Web MIDI API. This flag does not
control whether the API is exposed in Blink.

Name: kWebNfc
Documentation:
Kill switch for the WebNFC feature. This feature can be enabled for all sites
using the kEnableExperimentalWebPlatformFeatures flag.
https://w3c.github.io/web-nfc/

Name: kWebNotesDynamicTemplates
Documentation: Feature for enabling dynamic templates.

Name: kWebNotesPublish
Documentation: Feature for publishing Web Notes to the server.

Name: kWebNotesStylizeEnabled
Documentation: Main feature for the Web Notes Stylize project.

Name: kWebOTP
Documentation:
This is intended as a kill switch for the WebOTP Service feature. To enable
this feature, the experimental web platform features flag should be set.

Name: kWebOTPAssertionFeaturePolicy
Documentation:
Enables WebOTP calls in cross-origin iframes if allowed by Permissions
Policy.

Name: kWebOTPCrossDevice
Documentation:
Feature to allow devices to send/receive the sms fetch request from/to a
remote device through the SharingService.

Name: kWebOtpBackendAuto
Documentation:
Controls which backend is used to retrieve OTP on Android. When disabled
we use User Consent API.

Name: kWebOtpCrossDeviceSimpleString
Documentation:
Shows only the remote device name on the Android notification instead of
a descriptive text.

Name: kWebPayments
Documentation: The JavaScript API for payments on the web.

Name: kWebPaymentsExperimentalFeatures
Documentation:
Master toggle for all experimental features that will ship in the next
release.

Name: kWebPaymentsJustInTimePaymentApp
Documentation: Used to control whether allow crawling just-in-time installable payment app.

Name: kWebPaymentsMethodSectionOrderV2
Documentation:
Used to control payment method section order on payment request UI. Payment
method section should be put on top of the address section when this feature
is enabled instead of under it.

Name: kWebPaymentsModifiers
Documentation: Used to control the support for Payment Details modifiers.

Name: kWebPaymentsRedactShippingAddress
Documentation:
Used to control whether the shipping address returned for the
ShippingAddressChangeEvent is redacted of fine-grained details.

Name: kWebPaymentsSingleAppUiSkip
Documentation:
Used to control whether the Payment Sheet can be skipped for Payment Requests
with a single URL based payment app and no other info requested.

Name: kWebRtcAllow48kHzProcessingOnArm
Documentation:
Kill-switch allowing deactivation of the support for 48 kHz internal
processing in the WebRTC audio processing module when running on an ARM
platform.

Name: kWebRtcAllowWgcDesktopCapturer
Documentation:
When enabled we will tell WebRTC that we want to use the
Windows.Graphics.Capture API based DesktopCapturer, if it is available.

Name: kWebRtcAnalogAgcClippingControl
Documentation: Enables and configures the clipping control in the WebRTC analog AGC.

Name: kWebRtcAnalogAgcStartupMinVolume
Documentation:
Enables the override for the default minimum starting volume of the Automatic
Gain Control algorithm in WebRTC.

Name: kWebRtcExposeNonStandardStats
Documentation: If enabled, expose non-standard stats in the WebRTC getStats API.

Name: kWebRtcHideLocalIpsWithMdns
Documentation:
Causes WebRTC to replace host ICE candidate IP addresses with generated
names ending in ".local" and resolve them using mDNS.
http://crbug.com/878465

Name: kWebRtcHybridAgc
Documentation:
Enables the WebRTC Hybrid AGC configuration - i.e., AGC1 analog and AGC2
digital (see http://crbug.com/1231085).

Name: kWebRtcIgnoreUnspecifiedColorSpace
Documentation:
Causes WebRTC to not set the color space of video frames on the receive side
in case it's unspecified. Otherwise we will guess that the color space is
BT709. http://crbug.com/1129243

Name: kWebRtcLogCapturePipeline
Documentation: Whether we should log extra debug information to webrtc native log.

Name: kWebRtcMetronomeTaskQueue
Documentation: Whether WebRTC should use a metronome-backed task queue. Default: disabled.

Name: kWebRtcMultiplexCodec
Documentation: Enables negotiation of experimental multiplex codec in SDP.

Name: kWebRtcTimerUsesMetronome
Documentation: Whether WebRtcTimer should use the metronome source. Default: false.

Name: kWebRtcUseGpuMemoryBufferVideoFrames
Documentation: Use GpuMemoryBuffer backed VideoFrames in media streams.

Name: kWebRtcUseMinMaxVEADimensions
Documentation: Instructs WebRTC to honor the Min/Max Video Encode Accelerator dimensions.

Name: kWebSQLAccess
Documentation: Allow access to WebSQL APIs.

Name: kWebUICodeCache
Documentation: Enables code caching for scripts used on WebUI pages.

Name: kWebUIDarkMode
Documentation:
Whether to enable "dark mode" enhancements in Mac Mojave or Windows 10 for
UIs implemented with web technologies.

Name: kWebUIReportOnlyTrustedTypes
Documentation: Enables report-only Trusted Types experiment on WebUIs

Name: kWebUITabStripContextMenuAfterTap
Documentation:
Controls whether the context menu is shown on a touch press or a touch
tap gesture on the WebUI Tab Strip.

Name: kWebUiFeed
Documentation: Feature that causes the WebUI version of the Feed to be enabled.

Name: kWebUsb
Documentation:
Controls whether the WebUSB API is enabled:
https://wicg.github.io/webusb

Name: kWebUsbDeviceDetection
Documentation:
Enables runtime detection of USB devices which provide a WebUSB landing page
descriptor.

Name: kWebViewSurfaceControl
Documentation: Hardware Overlays for WebView.

Name: kWebViewThreadSafeMediaDefault
Documentation:
This is used as default state because it's different for webview and chrome.
WebView hardcodes this as enabled in AwMainDelegate.

Name: kWebViewVulkan
Documentation:
If webview-draw-functor-uses-vulkan is set, use vulkan for composite and
raster.

Name: kWebViewVulkanIntermediateBuffer
Documentation:
Used to debug Android WebView Vulkan composite. Composite to an intermediate
buffer and draw the intermediate buffer to the secondary command buffer.

Name: kWebViewZeroCopyVideo
Documentation: Used to enable/disable zero copy video path on webview for MCVD.

Name: kWebXr
Documentation: Controls whether the WebXR Device API is enabled.

Name: kWebXrArModule
Documentation: Enables access to AR features via the WebXR API.

Name: kWebXrHandInput
Documentation: Enables access to articulated hand tracking sensor input.

Name: kWebXrHitTest
Documentation: Enables access to raycasting against estimated XR scene geometry.

Name: kWebXrIncubations
Documentation: Enables access to experimental WebXR features.

Name: kWebrtcMediaCapabilitiesParameters
Documentation:
Used to set a few tunable parameters for the WebRTC Media Capabilities
implementation.

Name: kWebviewAccelerateSmallCanvases
Documentation: Enables small accelerated canvases for webview (crbug.com/1004304)

Name: kWindowOpenNewPopupBehavior
Documentation: Enables new behavior for window.open() and BarProp properties.

Name: kWindowPlacement
Documentation: Gates Multi-Screen Window Placement features and additional enhancements.

Name: kWindowPlacementFullscreenCompanionWindow
Documentation: Allows sites to request fullscreen and open a popup from a single gesture.

Name: kWindowPlacementFullscreenOnScreensChange
Documentation: Allows sites to request fullscreen when the set of screens change.

Name: kWinrtGeolocationImplementation
Documentation:
Enables usage of the Windows.Devices.Geolocation WinRT API for the
LocationProvider instead of the NetworkLocationProvider on Windows.

Name: kWriteBasicSystemProfileToPersistentHistogramsFile
Documentation:
Enables writing basic system profile to the persistent histograms files
earlier.

Name: kXsurfaceMetricsReporting
Documentation:
Feature that enables xsurface to provide the metrics reporting state to an
xsurface feed.

Name: kZeroCopyTabCapture
Documentation:
If enabled, the `getDisplayMedia()` family of APIs will ask for NV12 frames,
which should trigger a zero-copy path in the tab capture code.

Name: kZeroSuggestPrefetching
Documentation: Enables prefetching of the zero prefix suggestions for signed-in users.
